1
00:00:16,650 --> 00:00:17,897
I've made up my mind.

2
00:00:17,897 --> 00:00:19,119
I decided.

3
00:00:19,119 --> 00:00:22,489
- Wait, what?
- I'll marry you, mister.

4
00:00:22,489 --> 00:00:23,557
I love you.

5
00:00:23,557 --> 00:00:25,893
[Like a first love we've missed]

6
00:00:25,893 --> 00:00:27,661
How much is this?

7
00:00:28,395 --> 00:00:30,397
[The four of them, reunited after ten years]

8
00:00:30,397 --> 00:00:32,099
So, what are you into, Woo Bin?

9
00:00:32,099 --> 00:00:33,866
You, Sunny.

10
00:00:35,769 --> 00:00:37,638
I'm losing it.

11
00:00:37,638 --> 00:00:42,242
[Q. What do you mean to each other now?]
For me, Guardian was...

12
00:00:42,843 --> 00:00:45,078
Watching my...

13
00:00:45,078 --> 00:00:49,416
incredible costars up close,

14
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:51,618
[Bashful]
shooting with them,

15
00:00:51,618 --> 00:00:55,956
that was such a thrill for me.

16
00:00:55,956 --> 00:00:59,159
[With the costars she looked up to]

17
00:00:59,159 --> 00:01:01,127
You're good at this.

18
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:03,897
[Guardian meant even more to Go Eun]

19
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:05,499
Me too!

20
00:01:05,499 --> 00:01:07,701
Okay, taking the photo!

21
00:01:07,701 --> 00:01:09,603
I kept thinking

22
00:01:09,603 --> 00:01:14,274
how lucky I was to be working
with people this incredible.

23
00:01:14,875 --> 00:01:17,377
[Gong Yoo on Go Eun]
You all know Go Eun already,

24
00:01:17,377 --> 00:01:22,115
but she's super easygoing, really honest,

25
00:01:22,983 --> 00:01:25,319
and even though she's younger than me,

26
00:01:25,319 --> 00:01:27,421
she's always goofing around.

27
00:01:27,421 --> 00:01:29,689
[Guilty as charged]

28
00:01:31,458 --> 00:01:32,659
As for Dong Wook...

29
00:01:32,659 --> 00:01:35,562
[How Go Eun sees Dong Wook]
We're the kind of friends

30
00:01:35,562 --> 00:01:40,067
who can talk about anything over a drink.

31
00:01:40,067 --> 00:01:43,170
He really takes my problems seriously,

32
00:01:43,170 --> 00:01:44,838
worries about them right along with me,

33
00:01:44,838 --> 00:01:46,106
and even hurts for me.

34
00:01:46,106 --> 00:01:49,209
[Dong Wook, always there for her]
And I'm so grateful for that.

35
00:01:49,209 --> 00:01:51,945
Anyway, Dong Wook and I

36
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:55,983
really lean on each other

37
00:01:55,983 --> 00:01:58,051
and always root for each other.

38
00:01:58,051 --> 00:02:00,654
We know each other so well,

39
00:02:00,654 --> 00:02:05,325
we're just really close,
comfortable, and easy together.

40
00:02:05,325 --> 00:02:08,629
[How Gong Yoo sees In Na]
Whenever I see In Na,

41
00:02:08,629 --> 00:02:14,585
I'm reminded of how warmly
she sees everyone around her.

42
00:02:14,585 --> 00:02:16,603
When I'm around In Na,

43
00:02:16,603 --> 00:02:18,872
I turn into a five-year-old,

44
00:02:18,872 --> 00:02:20,307
like a total baby.

45
00:02:20,307 --> 00:02:23,276
What are you even talking about?

46
00:02:23,276 --> 00:02:27,648
She treats me like some adorable little baby,

47
00:02:27,648 --> 00:02:30,129
[Becomes a total baby the second In Na's near]
so I just start talking

48
00:02:30,129 --> 00:02:32,352
in this tiny baby voice.

49
00:02:32,352 --> 00:02:34,921
We're all different, different in our own ways,

50
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:36,790
- and that's what makes it more fun.
- Right?

51
00:02:36,790 --> 00:02:40,894
It's like we're kids again.

52
00:02:40,894 --> 00:02:42,029
What?

53
00:02:42,029 --> 00:02:43,196
- I'm getting nervous.
- Oh, come on.

54
00:02:43,196 --> 00:02:44,610
No matter the age gap,

55
00:02:44,610 --> 00:02:47,334
[Four friends who go way back]
it really feels like we're just friends.

56
00:02:47,334 --> 00:02:51,405
I think we've all just got a permanent place

57
00:02:51,405 --> 00:02:53,440
in each other's hearts.

58
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:55,475
It always feels like
the four of us are drifting along

59
00:02:55,475 --> 00:02:58,378
in one calm boat.

60
00:02:59,746 --> 00:03:02,601
[Four people who stayed close]
- The ocean! - Eun Tak.

61
00:03:02,601 --> 00:03:05,952
- "Let's go together."
- Let's go together.

62
00:03:05,952 --> 00:03:07,487
Do you remember that?

63
00:03:07,487 --> 00:03:08,989
That must be it, right there.

64
00:03:08,989 --> 00:03:10,157
Oh, there it is.

65
00:03:10,157 --> 00:03:14,795
[Retracing their old memories]

66
00:03:14,795 --> 00:03:16,263
This feels so weird.

67
00:03:16,263 --> 00:03:18,298
- It's exactly the same, wow.
- This feels so weird.

68
00:03:18,298 --> 00:03:19,499
It's exactly the same.

69
00:03:19,499 --> 00:03:20,667
Hand me the flower.

70
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:21,914
[Strict]
You have to add, "It's my birthday."

71
00:03:21,914 --> 00:03:22,903
It's my birthday.

72
00:03:22,903 --> 00:03:24,071
You're even doing the lines?

73
00:03:24,071 --> 00:03:25,806
[The memories still so vivid]
No way.

74
00:03:25,806 --> 00:03:27,908
This right here is happiness.

75
00:03:27,908 --> 00:03:29,755
Yeah, exactly, what could be

76
00:03:29,755 --> 00:03:31,511
- happier than this?
- Nothing.

77
00:03:31,511 --> 00:03:35,949
[Happier together, all four of them]

78
00:03:35,949 --> 00:03:38,318
- A drone.
- Oh, the drone.

79
00:03:38,318 --> 00:03:40,654
The weather's so nice.

80
00:03:40,654 --> 00:03:44,913
[What story will today bring?]

81
00:03:46,093 --> 00:03:50,209
[EP2. Everyone has a moment
when the divine lingered]

82
00:03:54,167 --> 00:03:56,570
This is so cute.

83
00:03:56,570 --> 00:03:58,672
Right, we go in through here.

84
00:03:58,672 --> 00:04:00,407
Oh, there's something here.

85
00:04:00,407 --> 00:04:02,142
- Open this.
- "Fairy appearance area."

86
00:04:02,142 --> 00:04:03,443
- Right?
- Yeah, fairy appearance.

87
00:04:03,443 --> 00:04:04,978
- This isn't working.
- No, you pull it. Pull.

88
00:04:04,978 --> 00:04:06,146
I'll pull it for you.

89
00:04:06,146 --> 00:04:09,416
- Pull the door.
- No, just squeeze through there.

90
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:10,684
[Skipping the red door for the fairy one]
After you.

91
00:04:10,684 --> 00:04:11,952
After you, go ahead.

92
00:04:11,952 --> 00:04:13,587
Go ahead.

93
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:16,456
[And so, they stepped into Goblin House]
- People with bags first. - Where is it?

94
00:04:16,456 --> 00:04:17,958
- I think we just head straight.
- After you.

95
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:20,560
- Is it this house? This one?
- Right up here, this one.

96
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:22,662
It's beautiful.

97
00:04:28,401 --> 00:04:30,503
It's beautiful.

98
00:04:32,672 --> 00:04:34,372
Huh?

99
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,077
What's this?

100
00:04:37,077 --> 00:04:39,279
- Goblin.
- Huh?

101
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,914
What was it again?

102
00:04:40,914 --> 00:04:42,816
- Wait, what is it?
- Look.

103
00:04:42,816 --> 00:04:46,423
"It's the same as
Goblin Kim Shin's house password?"

104
00:04:47,821 --> 00:04:50,569
[A note left on the door]

105
00:04:50,569 --> 00:04:54,000
[The passcode here is the same
as the one to the house Kim Shin lived in]

106
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,929
- Wait, what is it?
- Look.

107
00:04:55,929 --> 00:04:58,665
"It's the same as
Goblin Kim Shin's house password?"

108
00:04:58,665 --> 00:05:00,734
- 1004.
- Oh, right.

109
00:05:00,734 --> 00:05:03,370
- Really?
- Yeah, that's it, 1004.

110
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:05,539
Because we always passed through
without entering it.

111
00:05:05,539 --> 00:05:06,840
[So sharp]
Hey, Eun Tak.

112
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:07,841
- Amazing.
- Right.

113
00:05:07,841 --> 00:05:10,267
We went through it, so we never remembered it.

114
00:05:10,267 --> 00:05:12,471
- Oh, that's true.
- Yeah.

115
00:05:13,547 --> 00:05:16,195
What is this? This looks so cool.

116
00:05:16,195 --> 00:05:17,584
Hey.

117
00:05:17,584 --> 00:05:19,501
Hey.

118
00:05:19,501 --> 00:05:22,322
[Introducing today's Goblin House]

119
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:27,693
[A cozy living room]

120
00:05:29,596 --> 00:05:34,467
[With the blue sea captured inside]

121
00:05:34,467 --> 00:05:36,167
Let's see.

122
00:05:39,706 --> 00:05:43,242
The ceiling here's so low, it's so cool.

123
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:58,792
[Up the ladder, a cozy attic]

124
00:05:58,792 --> 00:06:01,027
Oh, there's another room here.

125
00:06:03,463 --> 00:06:06,421
[Across from the living room, a clean kitchen]

126
00:06:08,435 --> 00:06:14,433
[Through the door beside it, a cozy bedroom]

127
00:06:16,309 --> 00:06:20,575
[The Goblin House,
with a picture-perfect sea out front]

128
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,418
- What is this?
- Hey, what is that?

129
00:06:25,418 --> 00:06:26,486
Come look at this!

130
00:06:26,486 --> 00:06:29,756
This is hilarious.

131
00:06:29,756 --> 00:06:31,725
There's even a school uniform.
They've got everything.

132
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:33,393
- What is it?
- Look at this.

133
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:35,595
What?

134
00:06:35,595 --> 00:06:39,933
[A welcome surprise for the four of them]

135
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:45,245
[Eun Tak's diploma and exam slip]

136
00:06:51,544 --> 00:06:54,114
[The Reaper's ledger of souls]

137
00:06:54,114 --> 00:06:57,924
[A trace of Sunny's past life]

138
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:05,727
[A little world of Guardian, frozen in time]

139
00:07:07,694 --> 00:07:12,032
[Room for Guardian: The Lonely
and Great God 10th Anniversary]

140
00:07:12,032 --> 00:07:15,168
Hey, Go Eun Tak's exam ticket is here!

141
00:07:15,168 --> 00:07:16,937
[A piece of Eun Tak's youth,
kept all this time]

142
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:19,105
[2017 college entrance exam admission slip]

143
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:21,666
- Look at this.
- What?

144
00:07:22,809 --> 00:07:24,509
Right?

145
00:07:25,111 --> 00:07:28,815
This is mine, the uniform I wore
in Guardian is right here!

146
00:07:28,815 --> 00:07:33,320
[19-year-old Eun Tak's uniform]

147
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:39,284
[Eun Tak and the Goblin, ten years ago]

148
00:07:42,395 --> 00:07:45,332
We look so young.

149
00:07:45,332 --> 00:07:46,833
This is wild.

150
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:48,934
This is so wild.

151
00:07:49,536 --> 00:07:51,236
Right?

152
00:07:52,939 --> 00:07:57,911
[As if under the Goblin's spell,
they haven't changed]

153
00:07:57,911 --> 00:07:59,379
Wait, what's this?

154
00:07:59,379 --> 00:08:01,081
Aren't you two supposed to wear these together?

155
00:08:01,081 --> 00:08:03,083
What is this?

156
00:08:03,083 --> 00:08:04,918
- This is the one we wear together.
- This is Wang Yeo's!

157
00:08:04,918 --> 00:08:06,634
It goes with Wang Yeo's outfit.

158
00:08:06,634 --> 00:08:09,188
It's the pair to his.

159
00:08:10,223 --> 00:08:17,030
[The Reaper's past life "Wang Yeo,"
Sunny's past life "Kim Sun"]

160
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:20,633
[The costumes that hold their sad story]

161
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:22,347
The poetry book is here, "It was first love."

162
00:08:22,347 --> 00:08:24,237
"The Physics of Love"

163
00:08:24,237 --> 00:08:27,207
[The moment the Goblin first knew
he was in love]

164
00:08:27,207 --> 00:08:30,543
<i>The magnitude of mass isn't
proportional to its volume.</i>

165
00:08:32,412 --> 00:08:36,916
<i>From sky to earth,
the heart kept swinging in a dizzying pendulum.</i>

166
00:08:39,986 --> 00:08:41,954
<i>It was first love.</i>

167
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:46,893
[The iconic scene
where their fated love came together]

168
00:08:46,893 --> 00:08:49,362
The flower shoes are here too, look.

169
00:08:49,362 --> 00:08:53,499
Ripe persimmons, flower shoes, silk,
it's all here.

170
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,302
What was the line again?

171
00:08:57,003 --> 00:08:58,138
He gives her the flower shoes...

172
00:08:58,138 --> 00:09:01,007
[Fuzzy memory]
Ugh, I can't remember.

173
00:09:01,007 --> 00:09:03,243
- Ripe persimmons, flower shoes, one by one.
- Silk.

174
00:09:03,243 --> 00:09:04,911
- In a montage...
- Right.

175
00:09:04,911 --> 00:09:07,814
- In front of her...
- So I was...

176
00:09:07,814 --> 00:09:10,150
- I'd be at the chicken shop, and you'd come...
- Right.

177
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:12,485
bringing all those things so desperately.

178
00:09:12,485 --> 00:09:14,587
Right.

179
00:09:14,587 --> 00:09:17,557
[The Goblin,
reunited with his sister after 900 years]

180
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:19,225
These are the ripe persimmons you loved.

181
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:21,194
These are the flower shoes you always wanted.

182
00:09:21,194 --> 00:09:23,930
This is the color you liked.

183
00:09:23,930 --> 00:09:25,665
I don't like this color.

184
00:09:25,665 --> 00:09:27,100
I don't wear flower shoes.

185
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:29,435
[Even the Goblin didn't know his sister's taste]
I don't eat ripe persimmons.

186
00:09:31,154 --> 00:09:34,490
Huh? I actually brought my script.

187
00:09:36,142 --> 00:09:42,081
[The Guardian mementos
they kept all these years]

188
00:09:42,982 --> 00:09:45,151
- This is really...
- It's exactly the same, exactly.

189
00:09:45,151 --> 00:09:46,786
- Why is it so big? So many?
- No, but...

190
00:09:46,786 --> 00:09:48,221
It's big, and it's all still here.

191
00:09:48,221 --> 00:09:50,856
You kept it in such good shape.

192
00:09:53,359 --> 00:09:58,798
[The Reaper costume
Dong Wook kept for ten years]

193
00:09:58,798 --> 00:10:01,000
So I kept the whole thing, all of it.

194
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,735
- You kept this?
- Yeah.

195
00:10:02,735 --> 00:10:05,138
- Someday, I figured...
- This is so thoughtful.

196
00:10:05,138 --> 00:10:06,139
Seriously.

197
00:10:06,139 --> 00:10:08,108
I figured someday I'd get to show it.

198
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:09,175
Even the fedora's still here.

199
00:10:09,175 --> 00:10:11,377
- Put it on.
- It's so clean.

200
00:10:12,579 --> 00:10:14,314
[The Reaper, back on the job after ten years]

201
00:10:14,314 --> 00:10:15,849
Oh, you scared me.

202
00:10:15,849 --> 00:10:17,616
An unlisted soul.

203
00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:20,453
I think I put this on you backward back then.

204
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:23,223
[Instantly back in that scene]
Right, you put it on backward.

205
00:10:23,223 --> 00:10:25,091
Try it on, unlisted soul.

206
00:10:25,091 --> 00:10:26,559
- Let me try it on.
- Yeah.

207
00:10:26,559 --> 00:10:28,594
[An unlisted soul plays Grim Reaper]

208
00:10:29,629 --> 00:10:31,243
Now she's going to want this too.

209
00:10:31,243 --> 00:10:32,599
It looks good on you.

210
00:10:32,599 --> 00:10:33,900
It looks good on you.

211
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:36,970
[Sneaking over]

212
00:10:36,970 --> 00:10:39,601
"There he is. I found him."

213
00:10:39,601 --> 00:10:41,774
Look, this is exactly the same too.

214
00:10:41,774 --> 00:10:45,712
[Goblin brings the scene back]

215
00:10:45,712 --> 00:10:46,992
[A quick lore refresher]

216
00:10:46,992 --> 00:10:49,863
[The hat makes Reapers invisible]

217
00:10:53,019 --> 00:10:57,157
[Sunny exposes him with a peach blossom]

218
00:10:57,157 --> 00:10:59,993
[Reenacting the scene]
There he is. I found him.

219
00:10:59,993 --> 00:11:01,394
Look, this is exactly the same too.

220
00:11:01,394 --> 00:11:02,462
- Oh? This one!
- Remember it?

221
00:11:02,462 --> 00:11:05,498
- Of course I do.
- Let's try it on.

222
00:11:05,498 --> 00:11:09,954
[Another Reaper look, kept safe for ten years]

223
00:11:12,906 --> 00:11:18,906
[The leather coat that completed his icy look]

224
00:11:19,946 --> 00:11:23,116
[Trying it on]
That looks really stylish.

225
00:11:23,116 --> 00:11:25,784
Eun Tak's going to take everything again.

226
00:11:26,819 --> 00:11:29,722
Why are there two coats, though?

227
00:11:29,722 --> 00:11:31,958
- Is this the winter coat?
- Yeah, that one's the coat.

228
00:11:31,958 --> 00:11:35,028
- You kept everything.
- Everything's here.

229
00:11:35,028 --> 00:11:37,130
[A sleek black suit, the Reaper's go-to look]

230
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:38,865
[Leather coat for chilly fieldwork]

231
00:11:38,865 --> 00:11:40,900
[For fieldwork in freezing weather]

232
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,570
[This is peak Reaper style]

233
00:11:43,570 --> 00:11:47,507
- Even the vest inside is still here.
- Try it on.

234
00:11:47,507 --> 00:11:49,442
- It probably won't fit.
- Just try the jacket.

235
00:11:49,442 --> 00:11:51,377
- It looks so good.
- Why is it so tiny?

236
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:52,524
- Why is it so tiny?
- Clothes back then were...

237
00:11:52,524 --> 00:11:54,547
- Clothes were...
- Didn't you lose weight back then?

238
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:55,481
cut really slim and small like this.

239
00:11:55,481 --> 00:11:56,516
- Right.
- Yeah, that was the style.

240
00:11:56,516 --> 00:11:58,518
- What size is this, anyway?
- Were you really that skinny back then?

241
00:11:58,518 --> 00:12:00,787
Yeah. Because when we first started the show,

242
00:12:00,787 --> 00:12:03,835
they both barely ate

243
00:12:03,835 --> 00:12:05,725
- and basically starved themselves.
- Oh, right. In Canada,

244
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:07,527
- they were eating chicken breast and all that.
- Right, exactly.

245
00:12:07,527 --> 00:12:09,395
Is this even going to fit?

246
00:12:12,832 --> 00:12:16,302
- It's really small on you.
- It is.

247
00:12:16,302 --> 00:12:17,904
[Way too tight]

248
00:12:17,904 --> 00:12:19,572
It's seriously small on you.

249
00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:21,007
The sleeves...

250
00:12:21,007 --> 00:12:22,342
[Grim Reaper's gotten broader over ten years]
Are you still having a growth spurt?

251
00:12:22,342 --> 00:12:23,710
- It's just tight in the shoulders.
- Right.

252
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:25,111
- It's riding up.
- The back's so tight.

253
00:12:25,111 --> 00:12:27,213
- Yeah, that's not happening.
- See, your back got bigger.

254
00:12:27,213 --> 00:12:29,215
- Let me try it.
- Go ahead, try it.

255
00:12:29,215 --> 00:12:31,351
- You should take that one.
- I think...

256
00:12:31,351 --> 00:12:33,953
- This is your size.
- I think it'd look great on In Na

257
00:12:33,953 --> 00:12:35,622
- if she just draped it over her shoulders.
- Right.

258
00:12:35,622 --> 00:12:37,924
[In Na tries the Reaper look, too]

259
00:12:37,924 --> 00:12:39,259
You could totally pull this off.

260
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:42,862
[Made for In Na]
Okay, I'll take this one and you take that one.

261
00:12:42,862 --> 00:12:46,132
This looks really good on you.

262
00:12:46,132 --> 00:12:48,635
- It's pretty.
- Just take in the sleeves a little.

263
00:12:48,635 --> 00:12:50,937
"Take in the sleeves," my foot.

264
00:12:50,937 --> 00:12:52,905
Hey, Go Eun Tak.

265
00:12:52,905 --> 00:12:54,240
- It's a whole runway.
- Alright, let's see you walk.

266
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:55,508
- Both of you, walk it.
- It's a whole runway.

267
00:12:55,508 --> 00:12:58,305
[Say the word, and they're on it]

268
00:13:01,581 --> 00:13:02,749
Give me the sunglasses!

269
00:13:02,749 --> 00:13:04,617
Yeah, where is it?

270
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:06,686
- Give me the ones you're wearing.
- Okay.

271
00:13:06,686 --> 00:13:08,121
- Full black, all the way.
- Just perch them on.

272
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:09,856
[A model who nails every detail]
Perch them on.

273
00:13:09,856 --> 00:13:10,823
Hold on.

274
00:13:10,823 --> 00:13:12,292
Do these sunglasses look good on me?

275
00:13:12,292 --> 00:13:14,159
Yeah, they look really good.

276
00:13:15,501 --> 00:13:16,629
[Asking again]
Do they look good?

277
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:18,464
They look good.

278
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:20,366
- They look good.
- I walk from here? Like this?

279
00:13:20,366 --> 00:13:21,534
Walk back and forth.

280
00:13:21,534 --> 00:13:23,936
Just keep walking back and forth.
Let's just do what we're told.

281
00:13:23,936 --> 00:13:25,672
Wait, why is this...

282
00:13:25,672 --> 00:13:26,906
The pockets aren't even opened.

283
00:13:26,906 --> 00:13:28,174
Just pretend they're there.

284
00:13:28,174 --> 00:13:30,376
- Pretend they're there.
- Just like this.

285
00:13:30,376 --> 00:13:32,587
[Fully committed]

286
00:13:35,281 --> 00:13:41,281
[Reaper-core 2026 S/S]

287
00:13:42,221 --> 00:13:45,324
[Finished off with very human slippers]

288
00:13:45,992 --> 00:13:49,701
[Turning the yard into their own runway]

289
00:13:49,701 --> 00:13:51,297
And, action.

290
00:13:51,297 --> 00:13:53,599
"Action?" Why are you the one calling it?

291
00:13:53,599 --> 00:13:55,968
[Best seats in the house]

292
00:13:55,968 --> 00:13:59,405
- If you do that, I can't focus.
- Right.

293
00:14:00,106 --> 00:14:01,382
About-face!

294
00:14:01,382 --> 00:14:03,095
[Hup, two!]

295
00:14:06,779 --> 00:14:09,349
[The Reaper ladies strut in style]

296
00:14:09,349 --> 00:14:12,118
[Trying not to laugh]

297
00:14:12,118 --> 00:14:15,455
[Footage from Guardian]

298
00:14:15,455 --> 00:14:16,756
Do we look cool?

299
00:14:16,756 --> 00:14:17,990
- Huh?
- Do we look cool?

300
00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:20,026
Yeah.

301
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:21,094
Do we look cool?

302
00:14:21,094 --> 00:14:22,295
- Huh?
- Do we look cool?

303
00:14:22,295 --> 00:14:23,329
Yeah.

304
00:14:23,329 --> 00:14:24,731
Huh? Yeah...

305
00:14:24,731 --> 00:14:25,965
[Instant payback]

306
00:14:25,965 --> 00:14:28,334
- Okay, Ji Eun Tak, that's enough.
- How's this?

307
00:14:28,334 --> 00:14:29,769
Yeah, like this.

308
00:14:29,769 --> 00:14:31,336
[Another memory checked off]

309
00:14:32,638 --> 00:14:35,308
I still have my script, actually.

310
00:14:35,308 --> 00:14:37,043
- I don't have mine.
- You have your script?

311
00:14:37,043 --> 00:14:38,411
- I don't.
- You don't?

312
00:14:38,411 --> 00:14:41,080
Mine's somewhere at home too, probably.

313
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,583
- Oh yeah, our names ran down the page, right?
- Yeah.

314
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:47,320
[Yoo In Na kept her Guardian script]

315
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:50,423
It's all here, see?

316
00:14:50,423 --> 00:14:51,791
Hey, my autograph's in here?

317
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:53,326
Yeah, your autograph's in there.

318
00:14:53,326 --> 00:14:55,895
I saw it in there.

319
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:58,997
It was so nice to see it.

320
00:15:01,234 --> 00:15:02,535
This was all in here?

321
00:15:02,535 --> 00:15:03,770
[To In Na, working on this drama with you
made me so happy]

322
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:06,672
Everyone has such nice handwriting.

323
00:15:06,672 --> 00:15:08,441
Were there reshoots?

324
00:15:08,441 --> 00:15:10,576
There were quite a few reshoots.

325
00:15:10,576 --> 00:15:12,545
- There are notes all over this.
- Yeah.

326
00:15:12,545 --> 00:15:15,081
[Autographs and notes, all kept safe]
All the notes were still there from back then.

327
00:15:15,081 --> 00:15:19,051
And if you look at the back here,

328
00:15:19,051 --> 00:15:20,765
everyone's old autographs are still inside.

329
00:15:20,765 --> 00:15:22,388
- The last one, episode 16?
- Yeah.

330
00:15:22,388 --> 00:15:24,089
Right here...

331
00:15:25,691 --> 00:15:27,493
There's the writer's...

332
00:15:27,493 --> 00:15:29,974
[To my strange and beautiful guardians,
thank you so much]

333
00:15:29,974 --> 00:15:32,698
[Jan 10, 2017. Kim Eun Sook]

334
00:15:32,698 --> 00:15:35,601
Oh, this one was printed in.

335
00:15:36,335 --> 00:15:39,038
And yours. Right.

336
00:15:39,038 --> 00:15:40,273
See?

337
00:15:40,273 --> 00:15:41,319
[Our lonely and great time together...
may it stay a beautiful memory...]

338
00:15:41,319 --> 00:15:42,341
[I still can't quite figure it out.
Goblin Gong]

339
00:15:42,341 --> 00:15:43,709
[To my beloved Guardian team, thank you
for so much over all this time together]

340
00:15:43,709 --> 00:15:45,011
[I was so happy
and had such a great time being loved on set]

341
00:15:45,011 --> 00:15:46,212
[I love you all.
Go Eun Tak]

342
00:15:46,212 --> 00:15:50,267
[The cast's warmth, still in the final script]

343
00:15:50,267 --> 00:15:53,319
[Dong Wook. Let's keep in touch!]
There's yours, there's mine,

344
00:15:53,319 --> 00:15:55,321
Everyone has such nice handwriting.

345
00:15:55,321 --> 00:15:57,056
[I'll miss you all. Let's meet again.
I'll love you! In Na]

346
00:15:57,056 --> 00:15:59,025
- And there's Deok Hwa's too.
- Oh, yeah.

347
00:15:59,025 --> 00:16:00,092
Lee El.

348
00:16:00,092 --> 00:16:01,400
[I was so happy to be part
of this with you all. I love you!]

349
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:03,996
This was in here? How did I never see this?

350
00:16:03,996 --> 00:16:05,731
So this was in the final episode's script.

351
00:16:05,731 --> 00:16:07,800
Man, don't you miss these guys?

352
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:10,303
[Happy New Year. Kim Byung Chul]
Park Joong Heon was genuinely terrifying.

353
00:16:10,303 --> 00:16:12,104
- Byung Chul.
- He really put in the work.

354
00:16:12,104 --> 00:16:14,540
Hey, this is the Grim Reaper, right?

355
00:16:14,540 --> 00:16:16,375
The ghost.

356
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:17,844
- The junior reaper.
- These were all in here?

357
00:16:17,844 --> 00:16:19,779
- They were all there.
- Why don't I remember any of this?

358
00:16:19,779 --> 00:16:22,114
There are the reapers.

359
00:16:22,114 --> 00:16:24,584
See?

360
00:16:24,584 --> 00:16:26,619
All the reapers signed it.

361
00:16:26,619 --> 00:16:29,355
Kyung Hye, the ghost.

362
00:16:29,355 --> 00:16:32,658
- Oh, these autographs are so cute.
- Right?

363
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:35,294
So going through this
really brought it all back.

364
00:16:35,294 --> 00:16:36,463
The second I pulled it out...

365
00:16:36,463 --> 00:16:38,698
[Everyone's story, in one final script]

366
00:16:38,698 --> 00:16:40,967
- How did you keep all of this?
- Right?

367
00:16:40,967 --> 00:16:43,636
It just meant...

368
00:16:43,636 --> 00:16:45,438
[Yoo In Na, who's held onto these memories]
so much to me, this project.

369
00:16:45,438 --> 00:16:47,306
That's why I kept all of it.

370
00:16:47,306 --> 00:16:48,474
This is...

371
00:16:48,474 --> 00:16:50,676
really well kept.

372
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:52,611
Yeah, it really was.

373
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:59,485
But that door over there, isn't it wild?
So cool.

374
00:16:59,485 --> 00:17:01,454
- Where?
- That door there.

375
00:17:01,454 --> 00:17:03,189
- You open that, and you're in Canada.
- Quebec.

376
00:17:03,189 --> 00:17:04,690
Take me to Canada.

377
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:06,892
[This time, the crew heads for the red door]
Take me to Canada.

378
00:17:09,128 --> 00:17:10,730
[Following the Goblin...]

379
00:17:10,730 --> 00:17:12,865
I'm not done talking...

380
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:15,334
[The red door that took Eun Tak to Canada]

381
00:17:15,334 --> 00:17:19,038
Did you just come through that door?
Following me?

382
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,374
Do the "fairy appearance area" bit
one more time.

383
00:17:21,374 --> 00:17:23,075
"Tinker Bell!"

384
00:17:23,075 --> 00:17:24,577
Fairy appearance!

385
00:17:24,577 --> 00:17:25,945
[Appearing at Canada's fairy appearance area]
You met a fairy, remember?

386
00:17:25,945 --> 00:17:27,780
Tinker Bell.

387
00:17:27,780 --> 00:17:29,148
Tinker Bell.

388
00:17:29,148 --> 00:17:31,049
Tinker Bell.

389
00:17:31,717 --> 00:17:34,120
[A new Goblin House packed with memories]

390
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:36,556
This door is really something.

391
00:17:36,556 --> 00:17:37,890
You tried to follow through too, remember?

392
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:41,460
- But you couldn't get through.
- Yeah, that's right, I couldn't get through.

393
00:17:41,460 --> 00:17:43,762
Stay close, but not too close.

394
00:17:47,033 --> 00:17:48,346
[A quick lore refresher]

395
00:17:48,346 --> 00:17:51,304
[Only he could cross over,
so seeing his bride there stunned him]

396
00:17:51,304 --> 00:17:56,542
[Testing whether the Grim Reaper
can follow too...]

397
00:17:56,542 --> 00:18:00,712
[The Reaper can't make it through...]

398
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:05,117
[I'm the Goblin's bride, so of course I can!]

399
00:18:05,117 --> 00:18:07,501
[Bang]

400
00:18:09,234 --> 00:18:11,624
[Bang]

401
00:18:11,624 --> 00:18:13,834
[Turns out the Goblin's bride is pretty tough]

402
00:18:13,834 --> 00:18:15,328
[Funny just to watch]

403
00:18:15,328 --> 00:18:16,701
What?

404
00:18:16,701 --> 00:18:18,464
What?

405
00:18:18,464 --> 00:18:19,799
[Ten years later,
and Eun Tak still cracks the Goblin up]

406
00:18:19,799 --> 00:18:21,901
What?

407
00:18:21,901 --> 00:18:22,702
This is nice.

408
00:18:22,702 --> 00:18:25,638
- I'm just so excited.
- Oh, this is so nice.

409
00:18:25,638 --> 00:18:28,307
Look at these flowers! They're gorgeous.

410
00:18:28,307 --> 00:18:30,042
You sound just like my mom.

411
00:18:30,042 --> 00:18:31,811
Look at these flowers.

412
00:18:31,811 --> 00:18:34,267
Look, aren't they gorgeous?

413
00:18:34,267 --> 00:18:36,916
[Gong Yoo heads into the kitchen]

414
00:18:36,916 --> 00:18:42,488
[The grocery bag he packed from home]

415
00:18:42,488 --> 00:18:45,525
[Grunting]

416
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:51,931
[An endless parade of groceries]

417
00:18:51,931 --> 00:18:54,567
I ordered and packed the things

418
00:18:54,567 --> 00:18:56,902
- we couldn't get at the grocery store.
- Good call.

419
00:18:56,902 --> 00:19:00,419
I brought something
for our hangovers tomorrow morning.

420
00:19:00,419 --> 00:19:01,507
What?

421
00:19:01,507 --> 00:19:04,143
[He planned the menu down to the last detail]
Perilla oil, tuna fish sauce, soy sauce.

422
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:06,512
Looks like I brought pretty much everything.

423
00:19:06,512 --> 00:19:08,901
Well, you're the head chef, so of course.

424
00:19:08,901 --> 00:19:11,317
Let's lay everything out once we get there.

425
00:19:11,317 --> 00:19:14,586
[What's Chef Gong got in store?]
Whoa, why'd you bring so much?

426
00:19:15,801 --> 00:19:17,089
[Sorting out the groceries together]
We just stuffed ourselves,

427
00:19:17,089 --> 00:19:19,691
and now we're setting up more food.

428
00:19:20,393 --> 00:19:22,461
It's the aged kimchi!

429
00:19:23,329 --> 00:19:25,032
I simmered this for two hours at home.

430
00:19:25,032 --> 00:19:30,569
[The pork rib kimchi stew
Gong Yoo made at home]

431
00:19:30,569 --> 00:19:32,638
Perilla oil, and what's this?

432
00:19:32,638 --> 00:19:35,508
I want to use some sesame oil and soy sauce.

433
00:19:35,508 --> 00:19:37,977
- Bigfin squid tentacles.
- Bigfin squid, and...

434
00:19:37,977 --> 00:19:39,612
Glass noodles.

435
00:19:39,612 --> 00:19:41,947
This is olive oil.

436
00:19:41,947 --> 00:19:43,082
Korean sweet tomatoes.

437
00:19:43,082 --> 00:19:46,752
- Daejeo tomatoes.
- Yeah, Daejeo tomatoes are really good.

438
00:19:46,752 --> 00:19:48,287
Did you bring the seaweed too?

439
00:19:48,287 --> 00:19:50,856
Yeah, that seaweed is really good.

440
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:53,159
[Basically brought the whole kitchen]
This one's from a fan,

441
00:19:53,159 --> 00:19:54,493
and I brought it to try.

442
00:19:54,493 --> 00:19:55,928
Thought we'd have it with drinks.

443
00:19:55,928 --> 00:19:58,798
I'll put your gear over here.

444
00:19:58,798 --> 00:20:00,533
- Your gear goes right here.
- Sounds good.

445
00:20:00,533 --> 00:20:02,635
[Even packed his cookware]

446
00:20:02,635 --> 00:20:05,591
[Meanwhile, what's In Na up to?]

447
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:14,580
[Humming while hauling her bags]

448
00:20:14,580 --> 00:20:16,281
Chili peppers.

449
00:20:17,416 --> 00:20:19,418
You guys all came prepared.

450
00:20:19,418 --> 00:20:21,053
[Just as prepared as the Goblin]

451
00:20:21,053 --> 00:20:22,421
- But...
- Right, every little thing,

452
00:20:22,421 --> 00:20:24,090
- you brought all of it.
- Perilla powder.

453
00:20:24,090 --> 00:20:26,392
- Salt.
- Oh, we didn't have perilla powder.

454
00:20:26,392 --> 00:20:29,997
- Oh, perfect.
- Plus, there's no sesame grinder here.

455
00:20:29,997 --> 00:20:33,399
But look at this.
I ground the sesame seeds myself.

456
00:20:33,399 --> 00:20:35,768
- Here, smell this.
- This needs to be on camera.

457
00:20:35,768 --> 00:20:37,603
[Check this out]
- See? - Sesame seeds.

458
00:20:37,603 --> 00:20:40,949
[Our sweet little sister did all this]
In Na prepared all of this.

459
00:20:40,949 --> 00:20:42,241
Come here, look at this.

460
00:20:42,241 --> 00:20:44,577
Smell the sesame I ground.

461
00:20:44,577 --> 00:20:46,344
[Showing off]
What?

462
00:20:47,012 --> 00:20:49,115
It smells amazing.

463
00:20:49,115 --> 00:20:51,049
Here, you smell this.

464
00:20:52,351 --> 00:20:53,953
What is this?

465
00:20:53,953 --> 00:20:55,654
It's really good sesame.
Go Eun, come smell this.

466
00:20:55,654 --> 00:20:56,922
Does that go in the fridge, too?

467
00:20:56,922 --> 00:20:58,224
She ground the sesame so much.

468
00:20:58,224 --> 00:21:00,826
- It turned into oil.
- Does the perilla powder go in the fridge?

469
00:21:00,826 --> 00:21:02,728
[Gomtang]

470
00:21:02,728 --> 00:21:05,397
[Bigfin squid]

471
00:21:05,397 --> 00:21:08,968
[Chef Gong's pork rib stew with aged kimchi]

472
00:21:08,968 --> 00:21:11,804
[In Na brought veggies and more]

473
00:21:11,804 --> 00:21:15,708
[Plus kimchi from Go Eun's mom]

474
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:18,010
- He really came prepared.
- Right, he thought of everything.

475
00:21:18,010 --> 00:21:21,213
[The kitchen is fully loaded]

476
00:21:21,213 --> 00:21:22,915
This looks so pretty.

477
00:21:22,915 --> 00:21:24,450
It's not about how it looks,

478
00:21:24,450 --> 00:21:26,751
- it's the aroma...
- The aroma is amazing.

479
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:31,090
[They'll eat well for two days with all this]

480
00:21:31,090 --> 00:21:33,559
- Two ramen packs won't be enough.
- This squid is good.

481
00:21:33,559 --> 00:21:34,994
- Right? It's so good.
- Yeah.

482
00:21:34,994 --> 00:21:36,727
Squid.

483
00:21:37,596 --> 00:21:39,165
So how are we doing this?

484
00:21:39,165 --> 00:21:40,900
[Time to pick rooms]
Let's figure this out fast.

485
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:43,169
- Rooms?
- Yeah.

486
00:21:43,169 --> 00:21:44,982
[Goblin House has three rooms total]

487
00:21:44,982 --> 00:21:47,506
[1F room, 2F loft, 1F outer room]

488
00:21:47,506 --> 00:21:50,242
[Looking around]

489
00:21:50,242 --> 00:21:53,479
Should Go Eun and I sleep here?

490
00:21:53,479 --> 00:21:55,948
You two want to sleep together?

491
00:21:55,948 --> 00:21:56,982
The two of us?

492
00:21:56,982 --> 00:21:59,518
- We can share this one.
- Yeah, we don't mind.

493
00:21:59,518 --> 00:22:03,455
[Checking out the loft]

494
00:22:03,455 --> 00:22:05,825
If you two are fine sharing,

495
00:22:05,825 --> 00:22:08,260
you two take the biggest room,

496
00:22:08,260 --> 00:22:11,096
Dong Wook, you take this one,
and I'll take the outer room, right?

497
00:22:11,096 --> 00:22:12,164
I'm fine either way.

498
00:22:12,164 --> 00:22:14,567
[Gives the biggest room to the girls]

499
00:22:14,567 --> 00:22:17,970
Honestly, I could sleep on the couch, too.

500
00:22:17,970 --> 00:22:19,805
Try lying down. Does it fit you?

501
00:22:19,805 --> 00:22:21,240
It's soft and nice.

502
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:24,410
I could totally sleep here.

503
00:22:24,410 --> 00:22:27,413
Honestly, I can take the outer room.

504
00:22:27,413 --> 00:22:29,481
No way, that room scares me.

505
00:22:29,481 --> 00:22:31,083
- Why?
- Doesn't it freak you out?

506
00:22:31,083 --> 00:22:32,384
What's scary about it?

507
00:22:32,384 --> 00:22:34,587
Go in there alone.

508
00:22:34,587 --> 00:22:35,654
I played a shaman, remember?

509
00:22:35,654 --> 00:22:37,923
She's not the type to get scared.

510
00:22:37,923 --> 00:22:39,892
- You're really not scared?
- I played a shaman, remember?

511
00:22:39,892 --> 00:22:42,237
She was in Exhuma.

512
00:22:42,237 --> 00:22:45,066
Oh, right.

513
00:22:47,266 --> 00:22:50,369
[The outer room: bright and clean]

514
00:22:50,369 --> 00:22:51,837
- I like this one!
- Really?

515
00:22:51,837 --> 00:22:53,839
- Yeah.
- You want the outer room?

516
00:22:53,839 --> 00:22:57,142
Are you okay sleeping up there
with the low ceiling?

517
00:22:57,142 --> 00:22:59,345
[Doesn't mind at all]
Either way works for me...

518
00:22:59,345 --> 00:23:01,463
- I mean, it's just one night.
- Right, just one night.

519
00:23:01,463 --> 00:23:02,514
Right.

520
00:23:02,514 --> 00:23:04,717
I really can sleep on a couch.

521
00:23:04,717 --> 00:23:07,820
I sleep on my couch at home all the time.

522
00:23:07,820 --> 00:23:10,689
So what do we do?

523
00:23:12,524 --> 00:23:15,694
[The final call goes to the youngest]
Go Eun, where do you most want to sleep?

524
00:23:15,694 --> 00:23:17,563
Say you came here alone without us,

525
00:23:17,563 --> 00:23:19,865
where do you think you'd sleep?

526
00:23:19,865 --> 00:23:21,467
- Me?
- Yeah, you came alone.

527
00:23:21,467 --> 00:23:23,836
[What if Go Eun came here alone?]

528
00:23:23,836 --> 00:23:25,671
Here's what I think.

529
00:23:25,671 --> 00:23:29,041
- We take the outer room,
- Yeah.

530
00:23:29,041 --> 00:23:31,443
and the guys take the first and second floor.

531
00:23:31,443 --> 00:23:35,180
- I think that works better.
- Oh, there was a whole thought behind it?

532
00:23:35,180 --> 00:23:37,850
- And there's a separate bathroom, too.
- Okay, let's do that.

533
00:23:37,850 --> 00:23:39,385
As long as you're with me, I can sleep there.

534
00:23:39,385 --> 00:23:41,587
- I just meant I can't sleep alone.
- There's a bathroom here, too.

535
00:23:41,587 --> 00:23:46,759
But say In Na and I sleep downstairs.

536
00:23:46,759 --> 00:23:48,627
- Then one of the guys...
- Then the guys end up

537
00:23:48,627 --> 00:23:51,830
- has to sleep upstairs.
- sharing a room with the girls.

538
00:23:51,830 --> 00:23:54,433
So it's better if the guys split
the upstairs and downstairs,

539
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:55,734
- and we share one room.
- Right.

540
00:23:55,734 --> 00:23:57,503
- Yeah.
- Yeah, that makes sense.

541
00:23:57,503 --> 00:23:59,371
Exactly. No matter how close we are,

542
00:23:59,371 --> 00:24:00,873
we can't have guys and girls sharing a room.

543
00:24:00,873 --> 00:24:01,974
[Old-school gentleman]

544
00:24:01,974 --> 00:24:03,509
Go Eun and I will sleep out there,

545
00:24:03,509 --> 00:24:05,694
and you two can figure out
upstairs and downstairs.

546
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:06,938
[1F room: Dong Wook, Loft: Gong Yoo,
Outer room: In Na &amp; Go Eun]

547
00:24:06,938 --> 00:24:08,314
[Rooms are settled]

548
00:24:08,314 --> 00:24:10,482
- Then let's settle it like that.
- Sounds good.

549
00:24:10,482 --> 00:24:12,063
- That's the best setup.
- We're only splitting up

550
00:24:12,063 --> 00:24:13,252
- when we sleep, anyway.
- Right.

551
00:24:13,252 --> 00:24:16,021
- We'll be hanging out here until then.
- We should unpack first.

552
00:24:16,021 --> 00:24:17,323
Oh, right.

553
00:24:17,323 --> 00:24:20,458
Why do I not want to move at all?

554
00:24:21,327 --> 00:24:23,829
What are you going to wear?

555
00:24:23,829 --> 00:24:27,466
I only brought comfy clothes,
sweats, and pajamas.

556
00:24:27,466 --> 00:24:30,235
I can't just stay in pajamas the whole time.

557
00:24:30,235 --> 00:24:31,637
[A quick glance]
I'll save these for our guests.

558
00:24:31,637 --> 00:24:34,305
I'll just wear these pants.

559
00:24:34,907 --> 00:24:36,809
- Those look comfy.
- Right?

560
00:24:36,809 --> 00:24:38,210
- That's cute. What is it?
- Cute, right?

561
00:24:38,210 --> 00:24:40,612
I brought it from home to wear here.

562
00:24:40,612 --> 00:24:42,947
- It is a little big, though.
- It looks good on you.

563
00:24:44,717 --> 00:24:46,752
This is adorable, too!

564
00:24:46,752 --> 00:24:48,721
- Wear that one.
- Oh, this is so...

565
00:24:48,721 --> 00:24:51,390
Should I wear this? This is so cute.

566
00:24:51,390 --> 00:24:53,425
I brought something red, too.

567
00:24:53,425 --> 00:24:55,494
Right now...

568
00:24:55,494 --> 00:24:57,796
- that would be perfect.
- Wait, that's so cute.

569
00:24:57,796 --> 00:24:59,798
The shades are really similar.

570
00:24:59,798 --> 00:25:03,869
- They're both that vintage red, too.
- No way. This is actually insane.

571
00:25:03,869 --> 00:25:06,504
[Wait, what?]
It's like we planned this.

572
00:25:07,506 --> 00:25:09,641
- This one is so cute, too.
- That's cute.

573
00:25:09,641 --> 00:25:12,444
[Now the shopping really begins]

574
00:25:12,444 --> 00:25:14,179
This...

575
00:25:14,913 --> 00:25:15,814
You can swap with In Na...

576
00:25:15,814 --> 00:25:17,950
- This would look so good on you.
- Come on.

577
00:25:17,950 --> 00:25:19,597
Why are you pulling out all my clothes?

578
00:25:19,597 --> 00:25:21,820
Because your clothes are nice.

579
00:25:21,820 --> 00:25:24,222
[Gong Yoo's clothes are for sharing]
Seriously.

580
00:25:24,990 --> 00:25:26,837
- We should all...
- You two need to stop now.

581
00:25:26,837 --> 00:25:29,461
Come on, you two.

582
00:25:29,461 --> 00:25:30,963
I've decided. This is my look.

583
00:25:30,963 --> 00:25:33,332
[Dibs]
Come on...

584
00:25:33,332 --> 00:25:35,000
[Having fun with outfits]
Please stop already.

585
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:38,470
Why are you picking on me like this?

586
00:25:39,138 --> 00:25:40,706
Huh?

587
00:25:40,706 --> 00:25:43,575
- I'm going to change now.
- Okay.

588
00:25:44,576 --> 00:25:46,367
Oh, man.

589
00:25:46,367 --> 00:25:48,280
Oh, boy.

590
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:51,149
Even getting up here is a workout.

591
00:25:52,117 --> 00:25:55,421
You can't change up there.

592
00:25:55,421 --> 00:25:57,122
The ceiling's too low.

593
00:25:57,122 --> 00:25:58,624
How is a tall guy like him
supposed to change up there?

594
00:25:58,624 --> 00:25:59,858
Just change down here.

595
00:25:59,858 --> 00:26:02,994
Actually, it's kind of...

596
00:26:04,167 --> 00:26:05,834
[Ouch!]

597
00:26:05,834 --> 00:26:07,398
[Ouch!]

598
00:26:08,734 --> 00:26:11,912
[Cracking up]

599
00:26:11,912 --> 00:26:15,742
[Gong Yoo cracks everyone up]
Was that a sound effect just now?

600
00:26:15,742 --> 00:26:17,883
What did you hit?

601
00:26:18,544 --> 00:26:20,479
I knew that would happen.

602
00:26:20,479 --> 00:26:21,880
[That really hurt]

603
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:23,115
It's too low up there.

604
00:26:23,115 --> 00:26:24,434
What did you hit?

605
00:26:24,434 --> 00:26:26,767
Was that a sound effect just now?

606
00:26:26,767 --> 00:26:28,020
Seriously, what did you hit?

607
00:26:28,020 --> 00:26:31,190
[A rough encounter with the ceiling]

608
00:26:31,190 --> 00:26:33,201
[Baffled]

609
00:26:34,393 --> 00:26:36,228
Why did you even go up there to change?

610
00:26:36,228 --> 00:26:40,265
How am I supposed to change out there
in front of everyone?

611
00:26:40,265 --> 00:26:43,936
That was hilarious.
Just a loud thud and an "Ouch!"

612
00:26:43,936 --> 00:26:45,737
[Moving on from the minor mishap]
Seriously.

613
00:26:45,737 --> 00:26:48,807
[Time to go grocery shopping]

614
00:26:48,807 --> 00:26:50,708
Let's go.

615
00:26:51,910 --> 00:26:54,646
Is it okay that we didn't lock the door?

616
00:26:54,646 --> 00:26:55,747
Yeah.

617
00:26:55,747 --> 00:26:57,116
That counts as locking it.

618
00:26:57,116 --> 00:26:58,750
[Closing the red door]
Nobody can get in once it's closed.

619
00:26:58,750 --> 00:27:01,487
[Locking the door]

620
00:27:01,487 --> 00:27:04,088
- We're good since it's closed, right?
- Yeah.

621
00:27:04,990 --> 00:27:07,528
[Door secured, heading to the grocery store]

622
00:27:07,528 --> 00:27:09,228
What?

623
00:27:09,228 --> 00:27:12,264
[Letting out an old man groan]
Gosh.

624
00:27:12,264 --> 00:27:14,766
- Let's go.
- Does it really take 17 minutes?

625
00:27:14,766 --> 00:27:16,568
Yeah.

626
00:27:16,568 --> 00:27:18,704
Ramen, pork neck, and pork belly.

627
00:27:18,704 --> 00:27:20,873
Ice, snacks, eggs, and drinks.

628
00:27:20,873 --> 00:27:24,042
If anyone needs anything else
added to this list...

629
00:27:24,042 --> 00:27:25,144
just let me know.

630
00:27:25,144 --> 00:27:27,246
- In Na, do you have the card?
- Yes.

631
00:27:27,246 --> 00:27:28,313
I have it right here.

632
00:27:28,313 --> 00:27:30,949
You have to be my navigator.

633
00:27:30,949 --> 00:27:31,950
- I have to do it?
- I can...

634
00:27:31,950 --> 00:27:35,554
- I'm bad with GPS.
- Don't worry, I've got you from back here.

635
00:27:35,554 --> 00:27:38,257
Continue straight for 6.4 kilometers,

636
00:27:38,257 --> 00:27:40,625
then bear left.

637
00:27:42,027 --> 00:27:44,062
Do it in your real GPS voice.

638
00:27:44,062 --> 00:27:46,732
- Oh, right, In Na, you did the GPS voice.
- Right.

639
00:27:46,732 --> 00:27:48,800
Oh, yeah, In Na did the GPS voice.

640
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:52,204
In 6.1 kilometers, continue straight.

641
00:27:52,204 --> 00:27:54,606
In 6.1 kilometers, continue straight.

642
00:27:54,606 --> 00:27:56,208
[That voice!]

643
00:27:56,208 --> 00:27:57,543
- That's wild.
- Right?

644
00:27:57,543 --> 00:28:00,245
[The queen of GPS voices]
I recorded so much of it, over a few years.

645
00:28:00,245 --> 00:28:02,214
Right, I was fishing down in Jeju,

646
00:28:02,214 --> 00:28:04,434
heard your voice on the GPS, and I called you.

647
00:28:04,434 --> 00:28:06,351
That's you on the GPS, right?

648
00:28:06,351 --> 00:28:08,020
- "It's you, isn't it?"
- Over a few years?

649
00:28:08,020 --> 00:28:12,724
This was before voice tech got advanced.

650
00:28:12,724 --> 00:28:14,426
- So you had to record everything yourself.
- Yeah.

651
00:28:14,426 --> 00:28:16,662
[Back when they recorded syllable by syllable]
Yeah, we recorded everything

652
00:28:16,662 --> 00:28:18,697
and stitched it together.

653
00:28:18,697 --> 00:28:20,933
That doesn't happen anymore.

654
00:28:20,933 --> 00:28:23,735
AI takes all those jobs now.

655
00:28:24,469 --> 00:28:26,438
Mind if I put on some music?

656
00:28:26,438 --> 00:28:28,138
Sure.

657
00:28:28,941 --> 00:28:33,812
[Eddy Kim "You Are So Beautiful"
from the Guardian OST]

658
00:28:33,812 --> 00:28:37,049
[Love this song]

659
00:28:37,049 --> 00:28:43,021
Wasn't this the song
that played during our cute moments?

660
00:28:43,021 --> 00:28:45,224
- Yeah.
- Right.

661
00:28:45,224 --> 00:28:47,125
- You know, "pretty, pretty."
- Yeah, that's it.

662
00:28:47,125 --> 00:28:48,627
["You Are So Beautiful,"
also the Grim Reaper's favorite track]

663
00:28:48,627 --> 00:28:51,796
Pretty, pretty, I keep telling you,
why don't you believe me?

664
00:28:52,664 --> 00:28:54,266
- That was a song?
- Yeah.

665
00:28:54,266 --> 00:28:56,134
- You're basically quoting lyrics.
- I thought you were rapping.

666
00:28:56,134 --> 00:28:58,303
"Pretty, pretty, I keep telling you."

667
00:28:58,303 --> 00:28:59,538
Why won't you believe me?

668
00:28:59,538 --> 00:29:00,806
[What the Reaper was actually trying to sing...]
Just trust what I'm saying.

669
00:29:00,806 --> 00:29:04,543
<i>♫ You're really so pretty, so pretty ♫</i>

670
00:29:04,543 --> 00:29:06,678
<i>♫ I'm telling you, you're pretty ♫</i>

671
00:29:06,678 --> 00:29:09,081
<i>♫ Why won't you believe me, why ♫</i>
See, I was right, right?

672
00:29:09,081 --> 00:29:11,649
- I was right, right?
- Yeah, you're right.

673
00:29:12,884 --> 00:29:17,656
[Humming along to the throwback songs]

674
00:29:17,656 --> 00:29:20,592
[And they've arrived at the store]

675
00:29:20,592 --> 00:29:22,060
- All good?
- Yeah.

676
00:29:22,060 --> 00:29:24,663
- Getting out now.
- Time to shop?

677
00:29:24,663 --> 00:29:26,465
[The moment he steps out]

678
00:29:26,465 --> 00:29:29,968
[Opening the door like a gentleman]

679
00:29:29,968 --> 00:29:33,535
[Thanks, Dong Wook]

680
00:29:34,706 --> 00:29:36,701
You two look so cute together.

681
00:29:36,701 --> 00:29:39,467
- Really?
- You really look like a couple.

682
00:29:39,467 --> 00:29:43,448
[Even their outfits kind of match today]

683
00:29:43,448 --> 00:29:44,983
- Oh, hi there!
- Hello.

684
00:29:44,983 --> 00:29:46,018
- Hello.
- Yeah.

685
00:29:46,018 --> 00:29:50,589
- You're so handsome.
- Yeah, I know...

686
00:29:50,589 --> 00:29:52,601
[No false modesty from Dong Wook]

687
00:29:52,601 --> 00:29:54,667
- Must be nice.
- Did you see that?

688
00:29:54,667 --> 00:29:57,696
She recognized Dong Wook,
but not the rest of us.

689
00:29:57,696 --> 00:29:59,964
- I mean...
- That lady just...

690
00:30:00,899 --> 00:30:02,601
- She had no idea who we were.
- Yeah, no idea.

691
00:30:02,601 --> 00:30:04,002
What?

692
00:30:04,002 --> 00:30:06,438
She recognized you and Dong Wook,

693
00:30:06,438 --> 00:30:08,406
but not us.

694
00:30:09,341 --> 00:30:12,577
- Huh?
- That lady recognized you but not us.

695
00:30:12,577 --> 00:30:14,282
It's the sunglasses.

696
00:30:14,282 --> 00:30:15,681
[The whole crew cracking up]

697
00:30:15,681 --> 00:30:19,184
I always buy way too much at the store.

698
00:30:19,184 --> 00:30:21,053
- Hi there.
- I'll keep you in check.

699
00:30:21,053 --> 00:30:23,455
This is just for one meal.

700
00:30:23,455 --> 00:30:25,791
- Let's not waste money.
- No going overboard.

701
00:30:25,791 --> 00:30:29,913
[The crew's 10th anniversary grocery run]

702
00:30:29,913 --> 00:30:31,963
Should we grab the essentials first?

703
00:30:31,963 --> 00:30:34,041
What was on the list again? Eggs.

704
00:30:34,041 --> 00:30:35,734
- We don't need eggs.
- Yes, we do.

705
00:30:35,734 --> 00:30:37,369
- We need eggs?
- It's on the list.

706
00:30:37,369 --> 00:30:38,770
Eggs are on the list?

707
00:30:38,770 --> 00:30:41,239
[Ramen, meat, ice, In Na's snacks, eggs, drinks]
- Where is it... oh, there it is. - Eggs.

708
00:30:41,239 --> 00:30:43,508
Get the smallest pack,
but make it the good one.

709
00:30:43,508 --> 00:30:45,143
This one's the smallest.

710
00:30:45,143 --> 00:30:46,280
Let's get the good ones.

711
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:49,381
- What are they for?
- Snacks with drinks.

712
00:30:49,381 --> 00:30:51,550
- Fried in perilla oil, with soy sauce.
- Right, just fry them up.

713
00:30:51,550 --> 00:30:52,851
That sounds good already.

714
00:30:52,851 --> 00:30:54,868
- Yeah, get six.
- Six is enough.

715
00:30:54,868 --> 00:30:57,067
- Okay.
- We can't eat 12.

716
00:30:57,067 --> 00:30:58,390
[Eggs]

717
00:30:58,390 --> 00:30:59,758
Six.

718
00:30:59,758 --> 00:31:01,592
Where'd she go?

719
00:31:02,194 --> 00:31:03,195
Where did she disappear to?

720
00:31:03,195 --> 00:31:06,565
[Where did the youngest one disappear to?]
She said she was heading to the meat section.

721
00:31:06,565 --> 00:31:07,701
Meat.

722
00:31:07,701 --> 00:31:09,267
[Making a beeline for the meat]

723
00:31:09,267 --> 00:31:12,200
We should get thick-cut meat, right?

724
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:13,405
Right?

725
00:31:13,405 --> 00:31:15,374
Did we have rice?

726
00:31:15,374 --> 00:31:18,477
[On her own, she's a little lost...]

727
00:31:18,477 --> 00:31:21,079
[Gong Yoo finds the missing youngest]

728
00:31:21,079 --> 00:31:22,447
Did we have rice?

729
00:31:22,447 --> 00:31:23,749
- We have instant rice.
- We do?

730
00:31:23,749 --> 00:31:24,816
We don't need to buy any.

731
00:31:24,816 --> 00:31:29,121
Since you're cooking the meat,
check the thickness for me.

732
00:31:29,121 --> 00:31:32,157
[Before the grocery run]

733
00:31:32,157 --> 00:31:34,993
[Gong Chef studies the grill]

734
00:31:34,993 --> 00:31:37,162
How are you supposed to grill it on that?

735
00:31:37,162 --> 00:31:38,463
Even if we light it an hour early,

736
00:31:38,463 --> 00:31:42,134
pork shoulder cooks pretty fast,
but we're doing the pork belly whole,

737
00:31:42,134 --> 00:31:44,202
- so that'll take a while.
- He's got a plan.

738
00:31:44,202 --> 00:31:46,171
[Pork neck and belly on the grill tonight]
It's really good.

739
00:31:46,171 --> 00:31:47,672
Hi there.

740
00:31:47,672 --> 00:31:50,642
This one's thick. Isn't this the kind you want?

741
00:31:50,642 --> 00:31:52,210
This is for boiled pork.

742
00:31:52,210 --> 00:31:54,446
This thick cut's for boiled pork.

743
00:31:54,446 --> 00:31:56,448
[Nice thick pork belly spotted]
Yeah, this is what we need.

744
00:31:56,448 --> 00:31:57,749
Let me check the size.

745
00:31:57,749 --> 00:31:59,801
[Chef's inspection]

746
00:31:59,801 --> 00:32:01,920
[Very serious]
It's two pieces.

747
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,688
[Checking every angle]

748
00:32:03,688 --> 00:32:05,357
Yes, this is it.

749
00:32:05,357 --> 00:32:06,825
Then let's take this one.

750
00:32:06,825 --> 00:32:09,227
This has a lot of fat, though.

751
00:32:09,227 --> 00:32:11,095
That's a lot of fat.

752
00:32:11,997 --> 00:32:16,580
Excuse me, since the pork belly is
pressed down in the package,

753
00:32:16,580 --> 00:32:19,337
how thick is it, roughly?
Like, what's the actual thickness?

754
00:32:19,337 --> 00:32:21,873
So it comes as one long block
with a square cut, right?

755
00:32:21,873 --> 00:32:24,242
[Shape and size]
- That's right. - Got it.

756
00:32:24,242 --> 00:32:25,477
And for the pork neck...

757
00:32:25,477 --> 00:32:27,614
[Next up: picking pork neck for the BBQ]
Is this the pork neck?

758
00:32:27,614 --> 00:32:31,016
Could you slice the pork neck
about 1.5 to 2 centimeters thick?

759
00:32:31,016 --> 00:32:32,698
[Order taken]

760
00:32:32,698 --> 00:32:33,785
Sure thing.

761
00:32:33,785 --> 00:32:36,321
[While Chef Gong picks out the meat]

762
00:32:36,321 --> 00:32:38,957
- You want to check out the side dishes?
- Sure.

763
00:32:38,957 --> 00:32:40,492
- It's right over here.
- Side dishes?

764
00:32:40,492 --> 00:32:42,627
- Oh, they've got side dishes here.
- So for side dishes...

765
00:32:42,627 --> 00:32:46,131
- They've even got green onion kimchi.
- That looks good.

766
00:32:46,131 --> 00:32:48,366
[Side dish 2]
Like this, pickled chili pepper salad.

767
00:32:48,366 --> 00:32:50,836
[Side dish 3]
Think we can skip the fresh radish salad?

768
00:32:50,836 --> 00:32:53,872
[Snack shopping continues]
Should we get some chocolate snacks?

769
00:32:53,872 --> 00:32:54,873
Have you tried this one?

770
00:32:54,873 --> 00:32:57,642
This one's actually really good.

771
00:32:57,642 --> 00:32:58,510
Huh?

772
00:32:58,510 --> 00:33:00,212
[In Na's favorite snacks in a pack]
They sell them like this too.

773
00:33:00,212 --> 00:33:01,546
- Four of them.
- Oh, my.

774
00:33:01,546 --> 00:33:03,815
- If we have any left...
- We can take them home.

775
00:33:03,815 --> 00:33:06,852
[Added to In Na's treasure box]
We can just take them home.

776
00:33:06,852 --> 00:33:09,988
[Snack radar on full blast]
We need some salty snacks too.

777
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:12,023
- Like these?
- Yes, exactly.

778
00:33:12,023 --> 00:33:13,892
[Salty snacks are in]
That should do it.

779
00:33:13,892 --> 00:33:14,926
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

780
00:33:14,926 --> 00:33:16,695
Doesn't it feel
like we're going to get in trouble?

781
00:33:16,695 --> 00:33:17,929
[The treasure box is full]
Should we stop here?

782
00:33:17,929 --> 00:33:19,331
- This is a lot.
- You guys decide.

783
00:33:19,331 --> 00:33:22,000
Are we allowed to buy this much?

784
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:24,035
In Na, are you Shin-chan's dog, Shiro?

785
00:33:24,035 --> 00:33:27,138
- Shiro?
- Why are you buying so many Shin-chan snacks?

786
00:33:27,138 --> 00:33:30,509
- Are you really going to eat four bags?
- I've been eating these every day lately.

787
00:33:30,509 --> 00:33:33,411
[Her love for these snacks is unreal]

788
00:33:33,411 --> 00:33:34,946
Let's stay in Gangneung for a week.

789
00:33:34,946 --> 00:33:37,249
We could live off all this for a week.

790
00:33:37,249 --> 00:33:38,917
We don't need sausages, right?

791
00:33:38,917 --> 00:33:40,785
Why sausages? Are we grilling them?

792
00:33:40,785 --> 00:33:42,354
You guys will be full from the meat.

793
00:33:42,354 --> 00:33:44,289
We don't need pickled radish, right?

794
00:33:44,289 --> 00:33:45,657
- What would we eat pickled radish with?
- I mean, radish wraps...

795
00:33:45,657 --> 00:33:47,000
[The shopping list keeps growing]
We brought kimchi, remember?

796
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:48,827
- Right.
- Then we don't need radish wraps.

797
00:33:48,827 --> 00:33:50,653
- We don't need seaweed, right?
- I brought some.

798
00:33:50,653 --> 00:33:52,075
[Can we go home now?]
What about this...

799
00:33:52,075 --> 00:33:54,032
- They have the good seaweed too.
- We brought seaweed.

800
00:33:54,032 --> 00:33:55,733
Ice cream?

801
00:33:57,536 --> 00:34:00,071
[Giving in]
- Eggs. - Are we eating this now?

802
00:34:00,071 --> 00:34:01,339
Ice cream?

803
00:34:01,339 --> 00:34:02,741
[Nods]

804
00:34:02,741 --> 00:34:04,442
Which one?

805
00:34:04,442 --> 00:34:06,878
Hurry. I can't keep the freezer open long.

806
00:34:06,878 --> 00:34:09,014
- You can close it and look.
- Try closing it.

807
00:34:09,014 --> 00:34:10,882
It's see-through.

808
00:34:10,882 --> 00:34:12,384
I'll take a World Cone.

809
00:34:12,384 --> 00:34:14,252
- World Cone?
- Yeah.

810
00:34:14,953 --> 00:34:17,022
[Different picks, same Goblin crew]
I saw one earlier.

811
00:34:17,022 --> 00:34:18,456
Bbangddoa.

812
00:34:18,456 --> 00:34:20,592
Everyone picked something different.

813
00:34:20,592 --> 00:34:22,139
[Loaded up]

814
00:34:22,139 --> 00:34:23,361
Pass me the Bbangddoa.

815
00:34:23,361 --> 00:34:25,334
- Sure.
- I'm eating mine.

816
00:34:25,334 --> 00:34:27,699
[One bite for me]
Have a bite.

817
00:34:27,699 --> 00:34:30,508
[One bite for Dong Wook]

818
00:34:32,938 --> 00:34:35,140
[So precious]

819
00:34:35,140 --> 00:34:37,041
I'm seriously so happy.

820
00:34:38,276 --> 00:34:39,411
Here we go.

821
00:34:39,411 --> 00:34:43,114
[Shopping spree done, heading back]

822
00:34:43,114 --> 00:34:45,050
[4:30 PM]
It's already 4:30.

823
00:34:45,050 --> 00:34:47,118
Time really flies.

824
00:34:47,118 --> 00:34:48,286
We start cooking the second we get back.

825
00:34:48,286 --> 00:34:49,621
- Six o'clock.
- Yeah, right away.

826
00:34:49,621 --> 00:34:51,823
- Need to get the coals going first.
- Yeah, true.

827
00:34:51,823 --> 00:34:53,992
Just a thought,

828
00:34:53,992 --> 00:34:56,934
if we have a dry rub,

829
00:34:56,934 --> 00:34:58,263
Yeah.

830
00:34:58,263 --> 00:35:01,032
- that'd be great on the meat.
- Yeah, for sure.

831
00:35:01,032 --> 00:35:03,068
Or, skip the marinade and just...

832
00:35:03,068 --> 00:35:05,203
[Chef Goblin can't stop thinking about the meat]
Just, uh, what's it called...

833
00:35:05,203 --> 00:35:07,038
I think dipping it in sauce would be better.

834
00:35:07,038 --> 00:35:08,173
Yeah.

835
00:35:08,173 --> 00:35:09,674
You know what you're doing.

836
00:35:09,674 --> 00:35:11,009
I'll do my best.

837
00:35:11,009 --> 00:35:13,645
In Na, what...

838
00:35:13,645 --> 00:35:15,614
what year were you born again?

839
00:35:15,614 --> 00:35:18,049
Right now? Well, right now...

840
00:35:18,049 --> 00:35:21,252
[That's classified]
as of right now...

841
00:35:21,252 --> 00:35:23,888
- Don't ask her that.
- No, wait,

842
00:35:23,888 --> 00:35:25,657
I was just curious...

843
00:35:25,657 --> 00:35:27,826
Are you older, or is Lee El?

844
00:35:27,826 --> 00:35:29,801
Lee El and I are the same age.

845
00:35:29,801 --> 00:35:30,895
- Same age?
- Yeah.

846
00:35:30,895 --> 00:35:32,097
- Really?
- Yeah.

847
00:35:32,097 --> 00:35:34,232
I hope Lee El shows up.

848
00:35:34,232 --> 00:35:36,101
[Who's coming to the 10th anniversary party?]
I've got a feeling Lee El will come.

849
00:35:36,101 --> 00:35:37,836
- Yeah?
- Just a hunch.

850
00:35:37,836 --> 00:35:41,539
[Gong Yoo's predictions]
Yook Sung Jae, Lee El,

851
00:35:41,539 --> 00:35:44,009
and Yoon Kyung Ho. Those three. But...

852
00:35:44,009 --> 00:35:46,277
- I feel like those three could show up.
- I think...

853
00:35:46,277 --> 00:35:48,348
Sung Jae, for sure.

854
00:35:48,348 --> 00:35:49,349
- Really?
- Yeah.

855
00:35:49,349 --> 00:35:51,931
Whoever shows up, it'll be great to see them.

856
00:35:52,584 --> 00:35:54,185
Yoon Kyung Ho...

857
00:35:54,185 --> 00:35:56,021
I feel like Kyung Ho's coming too.

858
00:35:56,021 --> 00:35:57,989
[Kyung Ho, another face he's missed]

859
00:35:57,989 --> 00:35:59,403
Kyung Ho's actually...

860
00:35:59,403 --> 00:36:01,292
- a year younger than you, right?
- Yeah, a year younger.

861
00:36:01,292 --> 00:36:05,163
- At a movie wrap party a while back,
- Yeah.

862
00:36:05,163 --> 00:36:07,065
I ran into him.

863
00:36:07,065 --> 00:36:10,368
- Kyung Ho's doing really well now, right?
- Oh, absolutely.

864
00:36:10,368 --> 00:36:12,737
[Yoon Kyung Ho, thriving since Guardian]
We caught up, talked about old times,

865
00:36:12,737 --> 00:36:15,573
and I've been rooting for him the whole time.

866
00:36:15,573 --> 00:36:18,376
He's the kind of guy you just want to root for.

867
00:36:18,376 --> 00:36:22,013
It felt personal, in the best way.

868
00:36:22,013 --> 00:36:23,248
Yeah, totally.

869
00:36:23,248 --> 00:36:26,551
[Ten years on, still family at heart]
I told him I'm so happy for him.

870
00:36:26,551 --> 00:36:28,153
I love that scene.

871
00:36:28,153 --> 00:36:31,022
Secretary Kim gives him a house and a car.

872
00:36:31,022 --> 00:36:32,824
Right? Me too.

873
00:36:32,824 --> 00:36:34,434
This is your company apartment.

874
00:36:34,434 --> 00:36:37,362
[Woo Sik, the Goblin's loyal servant]

875
00:36:37,362 --> 00:36:39,397
This is your company-provided vehicle.

876
00:36:39,397 --> 00:36:40,932
For me?

877
00:36:40,932 --> 00:36:42,967
[Rewarded in this life for his past good deeds]
- Yes. - But...

878
00:36:42,967 --> 00:36:46,604
why are you giving all this to someone like me?

879
00:36:46,604 --> 00:36:48,906
You saved the country in your past life.

880
00:36:49,974 --> 00:36:51,409
I did?

881
00:36:51,409 --> 00:36:53,109
Yes.

882
00:36:53,978 --> 00:36:55,346
- Right?
- Yeah.

883
00:36:55,346 --> 00:36:57,816
You know how we always say someone must have

884
00:36:57,816 --> 00:36:59,563
had amazing karma in their past life?

885
00:36:59,563 --> 00:37:01,453
- We say that all the time.
- Right.

886
00:37:01,453 --> 00:37:05,356
Well, he actually literally saved a country.

887
00:37:05,356 --> 00:37:08,126
That scene really showed
Writer Kim Eun Sook's genius.

888
00:37:08,126 --> 00:37:11,262
She wrote that so brilliantly.

889
00:37:11,262 --> 00:37:13,231
Exactly.

890
00:37:13,231 --> 00:37:16,762
[In Na keeps on eating]

891
00:37:17,569 --> 00:37:18,903
[Cracking up]

892
00:37:18,903 --> 00:37:19,767
What is it?

893
00:37:19,767 --> 00:37:22,434
She's just eating that so happily.

894
00:37:22,434 --> 00:37:25,400
You really do love your snacks.

895
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:27,100
[Snacks are her specialty]
This is so good.

896
00:37:27,100 --> 00:37:29,133
But the bottom of the cone is the best part.

897
00:37:29,133 --> 00:37:30,601
- Right here.
- Yeah.

898
00:37:30,601 --> 00:37:31,934
- Do you want this?
- No, thanks.

899
00:37:31,934 --> 00:37:33,267
I can actually give this to you.

900
00:37:33,267 --> 00:37:34,601
Giving that away means
giving me the whole experience.

901
00:37:34,601 --> 00:37:36,801
It's true love if I give this to you, right?

902
00:37:36,801 --> 00:37:38,256
Give it to Eun Tak.

903
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:40,358
Giving that away is giving it all away.

904
00:37:40,358 --> 00:37:42,067
The chocolate at the bottom?

905
00:37:42,067 --> 00:37:44,534
Yeah. Who wants this?

906
00:37:44,534 --> 00:37:47,801
Eun Tak gets first dibs.

907
00:37:47,801 --> 00:37:49,868
- Have it.
- No, I'm perfectly fine.

908
00:37:49,868 --> 00:37:52,367
- Want this? You couldn't eat while driving.
- No, I'm good.

909
00:37:52,367 --> 00:37:54,167
- The chocolate part.
- No way, I can't.

910
00:37:54,167 --> 00:37:55,907
- He says no.
- And finally, to you.

911
00:37:55,907 --> 00:37:57,634
Do you want this?

912
00:37:57,634 --> 00:37:58,767
No, you just eat it. Seriously.

913
00:37:58,767 --> 00:38:00,345
- Can I really eat it?
- Of course.

914
00:38:00,345 --> 00:38:02,000
- Eat it.
- No regrets?

915
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:04,701
- No second thoughts?
- None.

916
00:38:04,701 --> 00:38:07,451
Oh, man.

917
00:38:08,100 --> 00:38:10,288
You can't just give the whole thing away.

918
00:38:10,288 --> 00:38:13,133
[In Na's generosity]
Do you mean it's okay to give it like this?

919
00:38:13,133 --> 00:38:14,859
[makes a happy 10th-anniversary prep]
We're here.

920
00:38:15,868 --> 00:38:17,567
[Putting the groceries away]

921
00:38:17,567 --> 00:38:20,300
- Here's the ice.
- Will all of this even fit?

922
00:38:20,300 --> 00:38:21,734
There should be one more bag in there.

923
00:38:21,734 --> 00:38:23,134
- Down here?
- Yeah.

924
00:38:23,134 --> 00:38:24,505
[Quickly putting the ice in the freezer]

925
00:38:24,505 --> 00:38:26,704
[Should we put the meat in too?]
The meat.

926
00:38:26,704 --> 00:38:28,509
We don't have to put the meat in the fridge.

927
00:38:28,509 --> 00:38:30,575
- Really? Because we're cooking it right away?
- Yeah.

928
00:38:30,575 --> 00:38:32,100
Makes sense.

929
00:38:32,100 --> 00:38:35,346
I guess we should get the charcoal going.

930
00:38:35,346 --> 00:38:36,367
- Hey.
- Yeah.

931
00:38:36,367 --> 00:38:38,516
Let's start the fire. We don't have much time.

932
00:38:38,516 --> 00:38:40,919
[The guys head out to prep the BBQ fire]

933
00:38:40,919 --> 00:38:45,300
[BBQ grill]

934
00:38:45,300 --> 00:38:46,491
No, that's not it.

935
00:38:46,491 --> 00:38:48,059
- What?
- No.

936
00:38:48,059 --> 00:38:49,794
Are you trying to start the fire?

937
00:38:49,794 --> 00:38:52,400
- Yeah, the charcoal.
- Right.

938
00:38:52,400 --> 00:38:54,332
- No, the pork neck cooks really fast.
- Hey!

939
00:38:54,332 --> 00:38:55,400
Gloves.

940
00:38:55,400 --> 00:38:57,968
- She says she has gloves.
- Yeah, I have them.

941
00:39:00,467 --> 00:39:02,273
You just saved my life.

942
00:39:02,273 --> 00:39:04,175
[Massaging Dong Wook's arm
with hands covered in charcoal]

943
00:39:04,175 --> 00:39:06,200
You're getting charcoal all over...

944
00:39:06,200 --> 00:39:09,514
- What do I do?
- Take off your sunglasses and look!

945
00:39:09,514 --> 00:39:10,934
[The Peach Couple's chaotic teamwork]
Hey.

946
00:39:10,934 --> 00:39:13,050
Take off your sunglasses and look!

947
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:16,067
Oh no, what do I do?

948
00:39:16,067 --> 00:39:17,555
Just wash it off later.

949
00:39:17,555 --> 00:39:18,734
[Anyway, the gloves
were successfully delivered]

950
00:39:18,734 --> 00:39:20,067
Do I put it in here?

951
00:39:20,067 --> 00:39:22,229
- Do you think this is enough?
- Just use all of it.

952
00:39:22,229 --> 00:39:23,928
- All of it?
- Yeah.

953
00:39:23,928 --> 00:39:25,263
Are we just using this fire starter?

954
00:39:25,263 --> 00:39:26,367
No, no. We have to add...

955
00:39:26,367 --> 00:39:27,732
- the charcoal on top now.
- With the charcoal.

956
00:39:27,732 --> 00:39:29,600
We have to use the charcoal.

957
00:39:31,002 --> 00:39:31,870
[Grunting]

958
00:39:31,870 --> 00:39:33,467
Don't try to force it.

959
00:39:33,467 --> 00:39:36,567
Just hold still.
Come on, what is wrong with you?

960
00:39:36,567 --> 00:39:39,176
- What are you doing?
- No, this is how you're supposed to do it.

961
00:39:39,767 --> 00:39:40,979
Oh, seriously.

962
00:39:40,979 --> 00:39:45,219
[Basically an old married couple]

963
00:39:45,219 --> 00:39:46,367
Hit it.

964
00:39:46,367 --> 00:39:48,355
[Supporting with her hands]
There you go.

965
00:39:48,355 --> 00:39:50,891
Smacking the bag won't help
while I'm trying to pull it out.

966
00:39:50,891 --> 00:39:53,224
I'm just trying to help it come out smoothly.

967
00:39:53,224 --> 00:39:55,693
[Just rubbing the bag]
I'm giving it a nice massage here.

968
00:39:55,693 --> 00:39:57,434
Hey, stop it.

969
00:39:57,434 --> 00:39:59,250
Just go over there.

970
00:40:00,111 --> 00:40:02,692
Don't fight, you two.
Will you two stop fighting?

971
00:40:02,692 --> 00:40:03,991
[Eun Tak plays peacemaker]
- Oh my goodness. - Here, look. Look.

972
00:40:03,991 --> 00:40:05,071
- Get it started.
- No?

973
00:40:05,071 --> 00:40:07,371
[Are they doing it right?]
Is this enough? Do you use this much?

974
00:40:07,371 --> 00:40:08,988
- This much?
- No, that's a bit too much.

975
00:40:08,988 --> 00:40:10,100
- Too much?
- Yeah, a little too much.

976
00:40:10,100 --> 00:40:11,779
- The charcoal...
- If the heat gets too high,

977
00:40:11,779 --> 00:40:12,886
the meat will burn.

978
00:40:12,886 --> 00:40:14,267
You just need to keep it around 150 to 180 °C.

979
00:40:14,267 --> 00:40:15,333
Take some out.

980
00:40:15,333 --> 00:40:16,906
- Take it out. Put it here.
- Just take a little out.

981
00:40:16,906 --> 00:40:19,086
[At Chef Gong's word, the charcoal goes back]
- Put it back. - Put it back.

982
00:40:19,086 --> 00:40:21,437
How many are there now?
How many should we take out?

983
00:40:21,437 --> 00:40:23,310
- Take out four more.
- No.

984
00:40:23,310 --> 00:40:25,710
- That's enough. This should do, right?
- Yeah.

985
00:40:25,710 --> 00:40:27,071
[Charcoal amount, approved by Chef Gong]
- Because even then... - Yeah.

986
00:40:27,071 --> 00:40:30,213
- Yeah, I think that's about right.
- Yeah, that's good.

987
00:40:30,213 --> 00:40:33,560
[Lighting the charcoal with a torch]

988
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:37,057
No, it's flaring up right now.

989
00:40:37,057 --> 00:40:40,544
- It takes a while for the fire to spread.
- Just a little like this...

990
00:40:40,544 --> 00:40:41,719
[Wait until the coals are fully lit]
It takes quite a while.

991
00:40:41,719 --> 00:40:44,697
We need to let it burn
like this for about an hour.

992
00:40:44,697 --> 00:40:46,712
- What?
- How about we make a highball?

993
00:40:46,712 --> 00:40:48,641
- Sure!
- Sounds good.

994
00:40:48,641 --> 00:40:51,228
[From chef to bartender]
What's this?

995
00:40:51,228 --> 00:40:52,362
- I brought it.
- Huh? Isn't this...

996
00:40:52,362 --> 00:40:54,296
the thing they use
when they say "drink the poison cup?"

997
00:40:54,296 --> 00:40:55,565
It's called a jigger.

998
00:40:55,565 --> 00:40:58,511
[A jigger measures cocktail ingredients]
When measuring liquor by the milliliter,

999
00:40:58,511 --> 00:41:00,626
- you use this for precision.
- Really?

1000
00:41:00,626 --> 00:41:02,265
[Equipment Chef Gong brought from home]
Bartenders use these

1001
00:41:02,265 --> 00:41:04,117
at cocktail and whiskey bars.

1002
00:41:04,117 --> 00:41:05,850
[Dong Wook is the assistant]

1003
00:41:05,850 --> 00:41:07,351
Could you open this for me?

1004
00:41:07,351 --> 00:41:08,533
- Gong Yoo.
- Yeah?

1005
00:41:08,533 --> 00:41:09,626
Could you add some ice?

1006
00:41:09,626 --> 00:41:11,535
- Okay.
- Okay.

1007
00:41:11,535 --> 00:41:14,789
[This time, making highballs
by following Bartender Gong]

1008
00:41:14,789 --> 00:41:17,666
[For a highball, the ratio is everything]
Wow, if you're measuring that precisely,

1009
00:41:17,666 --> 00:41:20,369
- there's no way it won't taste good.
- But...

1010
00:41:20,369 --> 00:41:23,428
the glass... is a little small.

1011
00:41:23,428 --> 00:41:24,441
It's okay.

1012
00:41:24,441 --> 00:41:26,452
- We're making them strong.
- We're fine with that.

1013
00:41:26,452 --> 00:41:27,801
We're making them strong.

1014
00:41:27,801 --> 00:41:30,394
We're all going down together.

1015
00:41:38,148 --> 00:41:41,350
[Cheonhyehyang]

1016
00:41:42,068 --> 00:41:43,841
It's so pretty!

1017
00:41:43,841 --> 00:41:45,328
It's not to make it look pretty.

1018
00:41:45,328 --> 00:41:47,480
[Gong Yoo BAR delights all your senses]
- It's for the aroma. - For the aroma, yeah.

1019
00:41:47,480 --> 00:41:49,474
- Really?
- I can already smell it from here.

1020
00:41:49,474 --> 00:41:51,634
- Is this mine?
- Yeah. This one's yours. Give it a smell.

1021
00:41:51,634 --> 00:41:55,166
- Wow.
- Now, like this...

1022
00:41:56,956 --> 00:41:58,021
Give it a little stir.

1023
00:41:58,021 --> 00:41:59,880
[Give it a gentle stir
so it mixes well with the ice]

1024
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:01,747
[Cheonhyehyang Highball complete]
This one will be sweet.

1025
00:42:01,747 --> 00:42:03,877
- Can I try it?
- Let's try it.

1026
00:42:03,877 --> 00:42:05,547
- Eun Tak!
- Yeah?

1027
00:42:05,547 --> 00:42:07,100
What are you doing?

1028
00:42:07,100 --> 00:42:09,554
[The youngest, Eun Tak, is freshening up]
I'll be right out.

1029
00:42:10,645 --> 00:42:11,827
Did you put on lip balm?

1030
00:42:11,827 --> 00:42:15,791
Oh, do you have to point that out?

1031
00:42:15,791 --> 00:42:17,364
Come on, what's the big deal between us?

1032
00:42:17,364 --> 00:42:20,571
[The definition of a real-life big brother]
Oh, you're so sweet.

1033
00:42:20,571 --> 00:42:21,772
Eun Tak!

1034
00:42:23,716 --> 00:42:25,701
That looks so good.

1035
00:42:25,701 --> 00:42:27,255
Alright, happy 10th anniversary!

1036
00:42:27,255 --> 00:42:28,818
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

1037
00:42:28,818 --> 00:42:30,058
Alright, let's have a great time today.

1038
00:42:30,058 --> 00:42:31,170
- Okay.
- Let's have fun.

1039
00:42:31,170 --> 00:42:34,164
- And no fighting!
- Yes, my dear sunbaes.

1040
00:42:37,043 --> 00:42:40,240
Why did everyone lose it at the same time?

1041
00:42:40,240 --> 00:42:41,691
- I've seriously never heard...
- Well...

1042
00:42:41,691 --> 00:42:44,565
[Nonstop laughs with these four]
- that before. - I didn't expect that from you.

1043
00:42:44,565 --> 00:42:47,280
You made it so, so delicious.

1044
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:49,660
[First toast, thanks to Bartender Gong]
Oh, it's so good.

1045
00:42:49,660 --> 00:42:52,214
- Alright, everyone, back to your own jobs.
- Okay.

1046
00:42:52,214 --> 00:42:53,807
- Alright, everyone, spread out again.
- Break up and regroup!

1047
00:42:53,807 --> 00:42:56,702
- Spread out, spread out.
- Spread out, spread out.

1048
00:42:56,702 --> 00:43:00,355
[Go Eun and In Na prep the vegetables]
- Want a cutting board? I've got one. - Really?

1049
00:43:01,427 --> 00:43:03,439
You're a great assistant.

1050
00:43:03,439 --> 00:43:05,058
Do it like this so it won't slip.

1051
00:43:05,058 --> 00:43:09,199
- I'll put this underneath for you, okay?
- Okay.

1052
00:43:09,199 --> 00:43:10,558
It won't slip!

1053
00:43:10,558 --> 00:43:12,548
[The smart part-timer helping the boss]

1054
00:43:12,548 --> 00:43:14,411
She's smart.

1055
00:43:14,411 --> 00:43:16,094
The kid's really smart.

1056
00:43:16,094 --> 00:43:18,669
No, no.

1057
00:43:18,669 --> 00:43:21,896
[The barbecue officially begins]

1058
00:43:21,896 --> 00:43:23,028
[Pork belly]

1059
00:43:23,028 --> 00:43:25,664
[Pork shoulder]

1060
00:43:25,664 --> 00:43:28,384
It shouldn't be over direct flames.

1061
00:43:28,384 --> 00:43:33,904
[Adjusting the spacing,
the details of a true barbecue expert]

1062
00:43:41,747 --> 00:43:44,864
Ah, that's strange.

1063
00:43:44,864 --> 00:43:46,515
The temperature should be
reaching 150 degrees...

1064
00:43:46,515 --> 00:43:48,418
[Worried]

1065
00:43:49,254 --> 00:43:50,954
This thing's been dead since earlier.
It won't go up.

1066
00:43:50,954 --> 00:43:51,987
Yeah, it's not catching.

1067
00:43:51,987 --> 00:43:53,841
[Restless, Chef Gong can't leave the barbecue]

1068
00:43:53,841 --> 00:43:57,755
[A stiff expression]

1069
00:44:01,808 --> 00:44:04,395
Look at him! Look at that stance!

1070
00:44:04,395 --> 00:44:09,069
[The back view of a man passionate about meat]
What's he planning to do with that stance?

1071
00:44:09,069 --> 00:44:11,819
Come on, heat up... Please.
It's not heating up. This is bad.

1072
00:44:11,819 --> 00:44:13,577
[A thermometer that won't even reach 100 °C]
No, no. It's because of that.

1073
00:44:13,577 --> 00:44:16,309
I think the thermometer's the problem.

1074
00:44:16,309 --> 00:44:18,524
We put in all this charcoal
and even fire starters.

1075
00:44:18,524 --> 00:44:20,543
How does it not even reach 100 degrees?

1076
00:44:20,543 --> 00:44:22,532
If this goes wrong, we're in trouble.
That's what I'm worried about.

1077
00:44:22,532 --> 00:44:24,232
No, it won't. It definitely won't.

1078
00:44:24,232 --> 00:44:26,152
[The calm Grim Reaper reassures Goblin]
If you're worried,

1079
00:44:26,152 --> 00:44:27,799
we can just slice it up and grill it.

1080
00:44:27,799 --> 00:44:28,851
- Well, that's true.
- Yeah.

1081
00:44:28,851 --> 00:44:31,958
- We'll just call this the first sear.
- Yeah, it doesn't matter.

1082
00:44:31,958 --> 00:44:34,199
It'd taste good even if
you cooked it in a frying pan.

1083
00:44:34,199 --> 00:44:36,024
[Full of concern]
Because it's already been smoked.

1084
00:44:36,024 --> 00:44:37,090
Alright!

1085
00:44:37,090 --> 00:44:39,479
[Meanwhile, In Na is in serious mode too]

1086
00:44:39,479 --> 00:44:43,424
[What's going on?]

1087
00:44:43,424 --> 00:44:48,564
[Knife skills that don't look very confident]

1088
00:44:48,564 --> 00:44:51,837
For the cucumber salad...
this should be okay, right?

1089
00:44:52,498 --> 00:44:54,176
Too big?

1090
00:44:54,176 --> 00:44:56,292
- Isn't this how you do it?
- How are you seasoning it?

1091
00:44:56,292 --> 00:44:58,334
You know, just mix it
with chili powder and gochujang

1092
00:44:58,334 --> 00:45:00,681
[Pretty chunky for a cucumber salad]
- until it's nice and red. - Yeah.

1093
00:45:00,681 --> 00:45:03,309
Honestly, I'm not very good at this, but...

1094
00:45:03,309 --> 00:45:04,637
[Truth is, In Na isn't much of a cook]

1095
00:45:04,637 --> 00:45:05,699
You'll figure it out.

1096
00:45:05,699 --> 00:45:07,478
[Worried, quietly steps in to help In Na]
- Does anything look wrong? - No.

1097
00:45:07,478 --> 00:45:09,401
- Nothing's wrong?
- No.

1098
00:45:10,285 --> 00:45:12,125
[Thinking over the recipe]

1099
00:45:12,125 --> 00:45:14,298
- Are the cucumbers good?
- Yeah.

1100
00:45:14,298 --> 00:45:17,990
- Should we sprinkle on a little salt first?
- Yeah, let's leave it for about ten minutes.

1101
00:45:18,883 --> 00:45:23,489
[As Go Eun suggested, sprinkle salt first
so the cucumbers absorb the seasoning]

1102
00:45:24,614 --> 00:45:26,071
[Soy sauce]

1103
00:45:26,071 --> 00:45:27,097
[Vinegar]

1104
00:45:27,097 --> 00:45:28,514
[Minced garlic]

1105
00:45:28,514 --> 00:45:29,716
[Gochujang]

1106
00:45:37,611 --> 00:45:41,452
[What kind of flavor is this?]

1107
00:45:42,451 --> 00:45:44,215
Oh my, Go Eun...

1108
00:45:44,215 --> 00:45:46,061
Oh my, Go Eun...

1109
00:45:46,061 --> 00:45:47,808
[Already filming,
Go Eun catches the perfect moment]

1110
00:45:47,808 --> 00:45:51,734
- Is something missing in the flavor?
- Oh, my.

1111
00:45:51,734 --> 00:45:54,160
In Na, I got all of that. You're so cute.

1112
00:45:54,160 --> 00:45:56,860
I can't believe you caught me doing this.

1113
00:45:56,860 --> 00:46:00,313
- You were suddenly so focused.
- Yeah.

1114
00:46:00,313 --> 00:46:03,660
I honestly felt so professional.

1115
00:46:03,660 --> 00:46:07,064
[Go Eun CAM]

1116
00:46:07,064 --> 00:46:09,513
[A hilariously scrunched-up face]

1117
00:46:11,730 --> 00:46:13,537
<i>Oh, my. Go Eun...</i>

1118
00:46:13,537 --> 00:46:18,448
[Perfect timing, how did you
manage to catch that? LOL]

1119
00:46:19,425 --> 00:46:21,259
Got you at the perfect moment, didn't I?

1120
00:46:21,259 --> 00:46:23,653
Why? What's wrong? Why?

1121
00:46:23,653 --> 00:46:25,465
So what's it like? Is it sweet?

1122
00:46:25,465 --> 00:46:26,532
- No. Way too...
- Is it sour?

1123
00:46:26,532 --> 00:46:28,506
- Sour! Yeah, it's sour.
- Stop, that's enough.

1124
00:46:28,506 --> 00:46:30,110
Okay.

1125
00:46:30,110 --> 00:46:33,209
Go Eun, please save this dish.

1126
00:46:34,140 --> 00:46:38,973
[In her past life, Eun Tak used to
cook for her aunt's family]

1127
00:46:41,023 --> 00:46:43,877
[She even had cucumber salad
experience in her past life]

1128
00:46:45,149 --> 00:46:49,447
[Will today's cucumber salad
make it to the table?]

1129
00:46:52,003 --> 00:46:53,384
What makes it sour?

1130
00:46:53,384 --> 00:46:55,856
[Drawing on memories from her past life,
checking the seasoning]

1131
00:46:57,523 --> 00:46:59,760
Did you add starch syrup?

1132
00:46:59,760 --> 00:47:02,766
- No.
- It says "starch syrup" right here.

1133
00:47:02,766 --> 00:47:04,845
[The recipe called for starch syrup]
- Huh? It said "starch syrup?" - Yeah.

1134
00:47:04,845 --> 00:47:06,731
Oh...

1135
00:47:06,731 --> 00:47:09,784
[Performing CPR]
Why didn't it turn out the way I wanted?

1136
00:47:09,784 --> 00:47:12,224
That's strange.

1137
00:47:13,519 --> 00:47:16,047
[Twitching]

1138
00:47:16,047 --> 00:47:18,780
Are you laughing?

1139
00:47:18,780 --> 00:47:20,640
- You are laughing!
- No, In Na...

1140
00:47:20,640 --> 00:47:22,540
[Couldn't hold back the laughter]

1141
00:47:22,540 --> 00:47:24,286
[It keeps coming back,
her hilarious scrunched-up face]

1142
00:47:24,286 --> 00:47:26,380
That expression was so cute.

1143
00:47:26,380 --> 00:47:29,339
- I'm losing it.
- Oh, this is so funny.

1144
00:47:34,177 --> 00:47:35,211
Still not there?

1145
00:47:35,211 --> 00:47:36,897
[Will today's cucumber salad be a success?]

1146
00:47:36,897 --> 00:47:39,683
[Go Eun gives it a pass]
- Well, I think it's good now. Try it. - Right?

1147
00:47:39,683 --> 00:47:43,983
- Because it should have a bit of tang.
- Right.

1148
00:47:44,978 --> 00:47:47,099
[Seasoning successfully revived]
- Yum! It's way better! - Yeah?

1149
00:47:47,099 --> 00:47:50,512
- It's good! Yum!
- Great.

1150
00:47:50,512 --> 00:47:52,002
Oh, it looks really good.

1151
00:47:52,002 --> 00:47:55,540
I think cutting the cucumbers
into big chunks was a good idea.

1152
00:47:55,540 --> 00:47:59,760
[Go Eun appreciates In Na's effort]
So you let me do it my own way?

1153
00:48:03,127 --> 00:48:05,695
[Their cucumber salad is complete]
It's done. I think it's done.

1154
00:48:05,695 --> 00:48:07,882
- I'll be the official taste tester.
- I think it'll be good.

1155
00:48:07,882 --> 00:48:11,099
[Taste test]

1156
00:48:11,099 --> 00:48:13,915
[This place makes great cucumber salad]
- It's good, right? - Yum!

1157
00:48:13,915 --> 00:48:15,321
- Is it good?
- Yeah.

1158
00:48:15,321 --> 00:48:17,688
Guys!

1159
00:48:17,688 --> 00:48:18,792
Yeah?

1160
00:48:18,792 --> 00:48:22,625
- In Na made the cucumber salad!
- Okay.

1161
00:48:22,625 --> 00:48:24,871
Come try it!

1162
00:48:27,801 --> 00:48:30,455
[How does it taste?]

1163
00:48:31,775 --> 00:48:34,581
- Yum, yum. Yeah.
- It's good, right?

1164
00:48:34,581 --> 00:48:36,186
- That reaction took a while though...
- What?

1165
00:48:36,186 --> 00:48:39,190
Why did you spend
three or four seconds thinking like that?

1166
00:48:39,190 --> 00:48:42,437
I'm just bad with spicy food.
I was figuring out whether it was spicy or not.

1167
00:48:42,437 --> 00:48:45,490
Alright. Still, that's not bad...

1168
00:48:45,490 --> 00:48:48,063
[Not a bad reaction from the second oldest]

1169
00:48:48,063 --> 00:48:49,604
[Hand-delivered straight
to the eldest brother at the grill]

1170
00:48:49,604 --> 00:48:50,785
What's this?

1171
00:48:50,785 --> 00:48:53,309
In Na made it.

1172
00:48:53,309 --> 00:48:55,000
- What do you think?
- That's it! That's the reaction!

1173
00:48:55,000 --> 00:48:56,821
- You've gotta go "Yum" right away.
- That's right. What do you think?

1174
00:48:56,821 --> 00:49:00,281
- I told you, I can't handle spicy food.
- It's really good.

1175
00:49:00,281 --> 00:49:03,456
It actually tasted terrible at first,
but Go Eun completely saved it.

1176
00:49:03,456 --> 00:49:06,949
- It's delicious now.
- No, I mean, it was seriously awful.

1177
00:49:06,949 --> 00:49:11,022
- Go Eun tasted it and fixed everything.
- It's tangy.

1178
00:49:11,022 --> 00:49:13,122
Ah, Go Eun Tak! I've got a job for you.

1179
00:49:13,122 --> 00:49:15,213
- You know how to make that, right?
- I've been working this whole time.

1180
00:49:15,213 --> 00:49:16,769
- Huh?
- I've been working this whole time.

1181
00:49:16,769 --> 00:49:19,742
I think you'd be great at this!
The minced garlic, pepper, salt... that one.

1182
00:49:19,742 --> 00:49:20,876
[An order comes in for Go Eun
to make the meat dipping sauce]

1183
00:49:20,876 --> 00:49:22,722
- The dipping sauce for the meat.
- Like the sauce from earlier?

1184
00:49:22,722 --> 00:49:25,315
Minced garlic, salt...

1185
00:49:25,315 --> 00:49:26,654
Yeah, minced garlic...

1186
00:49:26,654 --> 00:49:29,188
- Sesame oil!
- Sesame oil, exactly!

1187
00:49:29,188 --> 00:49:32,705
[A cooking genius can make anything]

1188
00:49:32,705 --> 00:49:34,319
[Add minced garlic]

1189
00:49:34,319 --> 00:49:36,639
[Salt]

1190
00:49:36,639 --> 00:49:38,979
[Pepper]

1191
00:49:38,979 --> 00:49:43,080
[Sesame oil...]

1192
00:49:43,080 --> 00:49:45,723
[Mix it all together with practiced hands]

1193
00:49:48,973 --> 00:49:53,613
[Expert vibes, wipes up the rest
with a clean finger]

1194
00:49:53,613 --> 00:49:56,287
The way your hands move when you cook...

1195
00:49:56,287 --> 00:49:57,999
[So much affection]

1196
00:49:57,999 --> 00:50:01,160
- No.
- You're just like a mom.

1197
00:50:01,806 --> 00:50:04,560
- Wow.
- Done? Think it'll taste good?

1198
00:50:04,560 --> 00:50:07,440
So good! It smells amazing!

1199
00:50:07,440 --> 00:50:11,136
[Go Eun's Meat dipping sauce complete]
- There you go. Thank you. - Wow...

1200
00:50:11,136 --> 00:50:12,274
I'll open it... shall I open it?

1201
00:50:12,274 --> 00:50:17,721
[How's Chef Gong's anxious meat doing?]

1202
00:50:18,530 --> 00:50:20,190
- Shall I open it?
- Yeah.

1203
00:50:26,451 --> 00:50:29,181
- It's done! The pork shoulder is done.
- There you go!

1204
00:50:29,181 --> 00:50:35,146
[Despite Chef Gong's worries,
it's cooking up to a beautiful golden brown]

1205
00:50:36,062 --> 00:50:37,450
- This one's done!
- Yeah.

1206
00:50:37,450 --> 00:50:40,529
- Hey, the foil! The foil!
- Foil! Foil! Foil!

1207
00:50:42,287 --> 00:50:47,167
[Pork shoulder and whole pork belly barbecue,
grilled with care for over an hour]

1208
00:50:50,709 --> 00:50:52,564
Should I line the plate with foil?

1209
00:50:52,564 --> 00:50:56,910
No, I'm wrapping it in foil!
To trap the heat and finish cooking it.

1210
00:50:58,274 --> 00:51:02,763
[Chef Gong's Tip: Wrapping cooked meat in foil
helps keep the juices inside]

1211
00:51:02,763 --> 00:51:06,921
[The care never ends]

1212
00:51:06,921 --> 00:51:09,386
[Pork belly needs a bit more time!]
- Ow, my eyes. - Yeah. It's all cooking.

1213
00:51:09,386 --> 00:51:10,825
The pork belly's coming along too.

1214
00:51:10,825 --> 00:51:13,259
- The pork belly takes a bit longer.
- Yeah.

1215
00:51:14,993 --> 00:51:17,646
[The Goblin family prepares
their 10th anniversary party together]

1216
00:51:17,646 --> 00:51:19,687
Then should we plate
some of the side dishes we bought?

1217
00:51:19,687 --> 00:51:22,612
- Yeah, let's plate this too.
- Alright.

1218
00:51:23,254 --> 00:51:25,858
[Hard at work]

1219
00:51:25,858 --> 00:51:28,318
[Almost time for guests]
It's really delicious.

1220
00:51:28,318 --> 00:51:30,762
What time are they coming?

1221
00:51:30,762 --> 00:51:33,598
Eun Tak, I'm gonna take a short break.

1222
00:51:33,598 --> 00:51:35,448
Are you going to drive?

1223
00:51:35,448 --> 00:51:38,721
- This is your last chance!
- I'm not! I'm not! I'm not!

1224
00:51:39,887 --> 00:51:45,887
[A quick break before the guests arrive
with an ice-cold beer!]

1225
00:51:50,915 --> 00:51:53,815
- Wow, it's the ocean!
- Wow.

1226
00:51:54,901 --> 00:51:56,089
Wow, it's the ocean!

1227
00:51:56,089 --> 00:51:58,217
[Heading toward Goblin House]
Isn't this place gorgeous?

1228
00:51:58,217 --> 00:52:00,754
- The weather's so nice today, isn't it?
- Right.

1229
00:52:00,754 --> 00:52:04,270
- Oh, there it is!
- Ah, here!

1230
00:52:04,270 --> 00:52:06,601
That's the door!

1231
00:52:06,601 --> 00:52:09,937
[Familiar guests arrive with memories]
- I don't know. Just go in. - Huh?

1232
00:52:09,937 --> 00:52:11,933
It's them!

1233
00:52:11,933 --> 00:52:13,473
- It is!
- It is! It is!

1234
00:52:13,473 --> 00:52:16,370
Oh, hello!

1235
00:52:16,370 --> 00:52:17,383
Hello!

1236
00:52:17,383 --> 00:52:19,509
- Oh, just like that!
- Hello!

1237
00:52:19,509 --> 00:52:24,095
[Passing through the red door,
old bonds meet again]

1238
00:52:24,095 --> 00:52:25,788
- Hello!
- Ah, Like this!

1239
00:52:25,788 --> 00:52:28,066
Hello!

1240
00:52:28,066 --> 00:52:31,105
Hello! El, hello!

1241
00:52:31,105 --> 00:52:33,886
[Running straight into a warm embrace]
- It's been so long! - Oh, my.

1242
00:52:36,087 --> 00:52:40,194
[Someone who stayed by
Eun Tak's side for so long]

1243
00:52:40,194 --> 00:52:42,094
[The guardian of the red thread of fate]
You've been through so much.

1244
00:52:42,094 --> 00:52:45,048
Your mom would be so proud of you.

1245
00:52:45,048 --> 00:52:49,160
[In the drama, the one who brought
countless fated connections together]

1246
00:52:49,160 --> 00:52:53,185
[The most charming Samshin, Lee El]

1247
00:52:53,185 --> 00:52:56,677
- It's been so long!
- Oh, my.

1248
00:52:56,677 --> 00:53:00,910
Oh my, Lee El, it's so great to see you!

1249
00:53:00,910 --> 00:53:02,770
[Another familiar face arrives]
Hello!

1250
00:53:02,770 --> 00:53:04,723
In Na!

1251
00:53:04,723 --> 00:53:08,229
Kyung Hye!

1252
00:53:08,229 --> 00:53:11,630
You little brat!

1253
00:53:11,630 --> 00:53:12,924
[An unforgettable presence in Guardian]
You little brat,

1254
00:53:12,924 --> 00:53:14,584
you never listen to a word I say, do you?

1255
00:53:14,584 --> 00:53:16,152
[The ghost who always stuck with Eun Tak]
Fine. I've been wandering this world alone,

1256
00:53:16,152 --> 00:53:17,904
so let's see how you like being alone.

1257
00:53:17,904 --> 00:53:19,598
[The Virgin Ghost, Actress Park Kyung Hye]

1258
00:53:19,598 --> 00:53:21,837
I'll kill that woman first.

1259
00:53:22,858 --> 00:53:24,978
Oh, my! Welcome.

1260
00:53:24,978 --> 00:53:28,837
[Then another familiar man appears]
- Hello, sir. - Yeah.

1261
00:53:28,837 --> 00:53:33,192
Wow, no way! Oh!

1262
00:53:33,192 --> 00:53:36,495
[The Goblin's ancient nemesis]
It's been so long! Wow.

1263
00:53:38,665 --> 00:53:44,665
[The evil spirit who sent
chills down everyone's spine]

1264
00:53:49,431 --> 00:53:51,374
In the end...

1265
00:53:52,504 --> 00:53:53,872
it's a catastrophe!

1266
00:53:53,872 --> 00:53:55,896
[The one who sparked the "catastrophe" craze]

1267
00:53:55,896 --> 00:53:57,555
Welcome!

1268
00:53:57,555 --> 00:54:00,637
- Welcome! It's so wonderful to see you.
- Great to see you.

1269
00:54:00,637 --> 00:54:03,658
Wow! We were just talking about you in the car!

1270
00:54:03,658 --> 00:54:05,344
[All are welcome, even old enemies]
- No way! - No way!

1271
00:54:05,344 --> 00:54:07,471
- Oh, Byung Chul.
- How do you look so much younger?

1272
00:54:07,471 --> 00:54:10,004
It's been a long time. What's with the sword?

1273
00:54:10,004 --> 00:54:12,501
[A sword in the villain's hand]
Oh, this.

1274
00:54:15,374 --> 00:54:19,322
[It fought alongside General Kim Shin
in countless battles]

1275
00:54:20,140 --> 00:54:24,554
[And ultimately pierced his chest]

1276
00:54:26,454 --> 00:54:31,301
[The Goblin's sword,
symbolizing his immortal life]

1277
00:54:32,406 --> 00:54:36,113
[And that very sword ultimately
destroyed Park Joong Heon...]

1278
00:54:36,113 --> 00:54:38,486
[Why do you have it?]
- What's with the sword? - Oh, this.

1279
00:54:38,486 --> 00:54:40,819
Well, I think...

1280
00:54:40,819 --> 00:54:42,772
someone left it behind ten years ago.

1281
00:54:42,772 --> 00:54:46,597
When I woke up, it was just lying next to me.
So I brought it back to return it.

1282
00:54:46,597 --> 00:54:47,846
[Brought it back as a souvenir?]
Wow, no way!

1283
00:54:47,846 --> 00:54:50,657
Wow, I never would've thought of that.

1284
00:54:51,617 --> 00:54:56,159
[The Goblin's sword returns after 10 years]

1285
00:54:56,159 --> 00:54:58,179
Kyung Hye, you came dressed
exactly like the Virgin Ghost!

1286
00:54:58,179 --> 00:54:59,365
- Yeah.
- Right.

1287
00:54:59,365 --> 00:55:00,985
[She brought back the Virgin Ghost outfit]
This is the actual outfit from ten years ago.

1288
00:55:00,985 --> 00:55:03,763
- You still had it?
- Ah, you wore it on purpose.

1289
00:55:03,763 --> 00:55:04,890
Oh, really?

1290
00:55:04,890 --> 00:55:07,404
I figured I wouldn't have
another chance to wear it,

1291
00:55:07,404 --> 00:55:09,256
so I wore it here, yeah.

1292
00:55:09,256 --> 00:55:13,264
I can't believe you kept it for ten years.

1293
00:55:15,093 --> 00:55:21,093
[Their first reunion in ten years
since the wrap party]

1294
00:55:23,684 --> 00:55:28,605
[A family reunited with shared memories]
Wow, this is crazy. It's just like back then.

1295
00:55:28,605 --> 00:55:30,198
Has it really been ten years?

1296
00:55:30,198 --> 00:55:33,393
- You all look exactly the same.
- Seriously.

1297
00:55:33,393 --> 00:55:37,111
- I made this welcome drink earlier.
- Wow!

1298
00:55:37,111 --> 00:55:38,512
[A welcome drink served with warm reunions]
As long as you don't dislike cinnamon,

1299
00:55:38,512 --> 00:55:39,529
- you should like it.
- Oh, welcome drink...

1300
00:55:39,529 --> 00:55:41,496
- Wow, thank you!
- Thank you.

1301
00:55:41,496 --> 00:55:42,630
Wow!

1302
00:55:42,630 --> 00:55:46,542
- Alright, welcome, everyone.
- Welcome!

1303
00:55:46,542 --> 00:55:50,259
[A truly special party with cherished friends]

1304
00:55:50,259 --> 00:55:51,298
Oh!

1305
00:55:51,298 --> 00:55:52,767
- It's good, right?
- Who made this?

1306
00:55:52,767 --> 00:55:54,032
Gong Yoo did.

1307
00:55:54,032 --> 00:55:56,425
- He sat here making these the whole time.
- It's so delicious.

1308
00:55:56,425 --> 00:55:58,332
I want the recipe for this!

1309
00:55:58,332 --> 00:56:01,932
[Gong Yoo's recipe everyone wants to share]
- Of course, I'll tell you. - Wow, it's good.

1310
00:56:02,562 --> 00:56:05,624
This is a welcome flower.

1311
00:56:06,299 --> 00:56:09,404
[Warm welcome with thoughtful gifts]
- A little welcome gift... - Wow!

1312
00:56:09,404 --> 00:56:13,998
Wow, isn't this a crocheted flower?
Did you make it?

1313
00:56:13,998 --> 00:56:16,252
Welcome!

1314
00:56:17,656 --> 00:56:21,401
Oh my, it's chilly.

1315
00:56:21,401 --> 00:56:24,346
[In Na steps into the living room for a moment]
Oh my!

1316
00:56:25,627 --> 00:56:27,161
[Rummaging around]

1317
00:56:27,161 --> 00:56:30,021
[Let's see...]
Where is it?

1318
00:56:33,437 --> 00:56:37,951
[She heads back out carrying extra clothes]

1319
00:56:37,951 --> 00:56:40,099
Won't you be cold? Aren't you cold?

1320
00:56:40,099 --> 00:56:41,684
- I think I will be.
- Honestly!

1321
00:56:41,684 --> 00:56:42,805
Won't you be cold?

1322
00:56:42,805 --> 00:56:44,285
- I think I will be.
- Aren't you cold? Honestly!

1323
00:56:44,285 --> 00:56:46,918
- You're right.
- I think this one will fit you.

1324
00:56:46,918 --> 00:56:48,246
Here, put this on.

1325
00:56:48,246 --> 00:56:50,073
Ms. Lee El, you wear the red one.

1326
00:56:50,073 --> 00:56:51,574
[Sharing warmth against the chilly night air]
And Kyung Hye...

1327
00:56:51,574 --> 00:56:54,536
I have something else that'll look
perfect on you. I'll give that to you.

1328
00:56:54,536 --> 00:56:56,955
[Touched]
- Thank you. - Put this on.

1329
00:56:56,955 --> 00:57:00,073
I think you're going to get really cold.

1330
00:57:00,073 --> 00:57:03,274
[Samshin Red equipped]
Oh! Your lipstick looks so pretty right now.

1331
00:57:03,274 --> 00:57:05,292
You look so pretty.

1332
00:57:05,292 --> 00:57:07,140
Isn't this kind of the trend these days?

1333
00:57:07,140 --> 00:57:09,292
- It's so pretty.
- My dear.

1334
00:57:11,140 --> 00:57:12,886
[Samshin's signature line: "My dear."]
"My dear."

1335
00:57:12,886 --> 00:57:13,954
My dear.

1336
00:57:13,954 --> 00:57:16,006
My dear.

1337
00:57:16,006 --> 00:57:20,504
[Two syllables that awaken memories]

1338
00:57:20,504 --> 00:57:23,605
Who laughs this silly?

1339
00:57:23,605 --> 00:57:24,980
[Preparing dinner amid happy chaos]
- Isn't that Kyung Hye? - Huh?

1340
00:57:24,980 --> 00:57:27,154
Isn't that Kyung Hye?

1341
00:57:27,154 --> 00:57:30,748
First, I should cut out the best parts.

1342
00:57:31,807 --> 00:57:36,501
[Selecting the best cuts]

1343
00:57:38,394 --> 00:57:43,203
[Checking the doneness of the meat]

1344
00:57:43,203 --> 00:57:46,150
- Sit down quickly and try this first.
- Yeah.

1345
00:57:46,150 --> 00:57:47,752
This is pork shoulder. Where should I put it?

1346
00:57:47,752 --> 00:57:51,544
- Wow!
- Hey, you have to eat it now.

1347
00:57:53,265 --> 00:57:55,158
- Oh!
- Wow!

1348
00:57:55,158 --> 00:57:56,659
This is amazing.

1349
00:57:56,659 --> 00:57:58,298
[Introducing today's feast for the family]

1350
00:57:58,298 --> 00:58:00,504
Wow, it's cooked perfectly.

1351
00:58:00,504 --> 00:58:02,289
[Chef Gong's first dish,
smoked pork shoulder barbecue]

1352
00:58:02,289 --> 00:58:03,943
I think it would be amazing
wrapped in kimchi with the meat.

1353
00:58:03,943 --> 00:58:06,058
- Exactly! Wow!
- Oh!

1354
00:58:06,058 --> 00:58:08,410
[In Na &amp; Go Eun's cucumber salad]
- It looks like something special. - Wow!

1355
00:58:08,410 --> 00:58:11,250
- In Na, I'm really looking forward to this.
- It's really good, right?

1356
00:58:11,250 --> 00:58:13,176
- It's almost simmered through.
- That's what makes it delicious.

1357
00:58:13,176 --> 00:58:15,794
Right, that's why I cooked it at home first.

1358
00:58:15,794 --> 00:58:19,014
- Braised ribs with kimchi...
- It's kimchi stew.

1359
00:58:19,794 --> 00:58:22,589
[A special feast with everyone]
Alright, let's eat. Let's eat while it's hot.

1360
00:58:22,589 --> 00:58:24,496
Because he really worked hard
grilling the meat.

1361
00:58:24,496 --> 00:58:27,009
- That's right.
- Thank you for the meal!

1362
00:58:27,009 --> 00:58:28,795
- Eat it while it's warm.
- Wow... he really went all out.

1363
00:58:28,795 --> 00:58:31,833
[Carefully grilled for one hour,
crispy outside and juicy inside]

1364
00:58:35,512 --> 00:58:38,278
[Instantly wins everyone's taste buds]

1365
00:58:38,278 --> 00:58:41,471
- It's good, right?
- It's so good! It's really delicious.

1366
00:58:41,471 --> 00:58:43,447
Wow, it's so tender.

1367
00:58:43,447 --> 00:58:45,913
[Approved]
Yum.

1368
00:58:45,913 --> 00:58:48,873
- This is yours.
- Go Eun made this.

1369
00:58:48,873 --> 00:58:52,079
[Pork shoulder with Go Eun's special sauce]
Put lots of it on and enjoy.

1370
00:58:55,128 --> 00:58:58,437
- Yum!
- It's so good, right?

1371
00:58:58,437 --> 00:59:02,131
It's been so long since I've had
barbecue like this. Wow!

1372
00:59:02,131 --> 00:59:04,958
[Chef Gong's pork neck was worth every minute]
They spent one or two hours on this.

1373
00:59:04,958 --> 00:59:07,818
That's right. Gong Yoo really worked hard.

1374
00:59:07,818 --> 00:59:09,252
The special sauce is really good.

1375
00:59:09,252 --> 00:59:10,710
[Even Go Eun's sauce adds
extra flavor to the meat]

1376
00:59:10,710 --> 00:59:12,501
- There's nothing special.
- Really?

1377
00:59:12,501 --> 00:59:14,175
Just minced garlic...

1378
00:59:14,175 --> 00:59:16,868
sesame oil, salt, and pepper.

1379
00:59:16,868 --> 00:59:18,054
- That's it?
- Yeah.

1380
00:59:18,054 --> 00:59:20,892
You just have to get the salt balance right.

1381
00:59:20,892 --> 00:59:23,404
If you make it too salty...

1382
00:59:26,398 --> 00:59:29,011
- This cucumber kimchi...
- In Na made this.

1383
00:59:29,011 --> 00:59:32,002
I made it and completely messed it up,

1384
00:59:32,002 --> 00:59:35,205
but Go Eun saved it. Just try one bite.

1385
00:59:35,883 --> 00:59:39,848
[In Na started it, Go Eun finished it]
It was honestly as sour as a lemon. Try this.

1386
00:59:45,399 --> 00:59:48,515
- Oh, the cucumber is so good.
- Go Eun, it's not sour at all.

1387
00:59:48,515 --> 00:59:53,518
[The Goblin family's official seasoning expert]

1388
00:59:53,518 --> 00:59:56,420
The special sauce is so good.
I want to take some home.

1389
00:59:56,420 --> 00:59:57,560
Which one?

1390
00:59:57,560 --> 01:00:00,766
- How's the cucumber?
- I already packed some cucumbers in my pocket.

1391
01:00:00,766 --> 01:00:03,300
I pretended to eat and
slipped a few into my pocket.

1392
01:00:03,300 --> 01:00:05,553
[A spoonful of wit
that brightens everyone's mood]

1393
01:00:06,693 --> 01:00:07,987
But seeing us all here like this

1394
01:00:07,987 --> 01:00:09,616
- feels so amazing.
- It's amazing.

1395
01:00:09,616 --> 01:00:12,982
- It's really unbelievable.
- It's been so long since I saw everyone.

1396
01:00:12,982 --> 01:00:15,030
- Yeah.
- Everyone is exactly like back then.

1397
01:00:15,030 --> 01:00:17,277
You really are the same.
It's amazing how unchanged everyone is.

1398
01:00:17,277 --> 01:00:21,142
Actually, we barely met... on set.

1399
01:00:21,142 --> 01:00:22,953
I never even met Kyung Hye and Byung Chul.

1400
01:00:22,953 --> 01:00:25,789
Seeing everyone together like this,

1401
01:00:25,789 --> 01:00:28,167
that closeness just comes back.

1402
01:00:28,167 --> 01:00:29,379
Right.

1403
01:00:29,379 --> 01:00:33,584
You know how seeing
familiar faces in a drama or movie

1404
01:00:33,584 --> 01:00:35,844
[Goblin connection as strong as school ties]
- just makes me extra happy. - Right.

1405
01:00:35,844 --> 01:00:38,284
- Right.
- That's so true.

1406
01:00:38,284 --> 01:00:39,812
I still remember meeting you

1407
01:00:39,812 --> 01:00:43,297
- at a premiere after the drama ended.
- Yeah, we met then.

1408
01:00:43,297 --> 01:00:45,850
You were so warm to me.

1409
01:00:45,850 --> 01:00:47,549
- You said you were so happy to see me
- Yeah.

1410
01:00:47,549 --> 01:00:49,479
- and that you enjoyed watching me.
- I was really

1411
01:00:49,479 --> 01:00:52,247
[In Na's kindness stayed with Lee El]
immersed in it back then when I saw you.

1412
01:00:52,247 --> 01:00:54,979
I was really just a minor character.

1413
01:00:54,979 --> 01:00:58,054
I didn't get to meet many
of the other cast members,

1414
01:00:58,054 --> 01:01:01,462
and I didn't really get close to anyone.

1415
01:01:01,462 --> 01:01:04,278
Really? That's so surprising.

1416
01:01:04,278 --> 01:01:08,657
- That's why I'm still so grateful.
- Really?

1417
01:01:10,653 --> 01:01:13,090
[While warm greetings are exchanged]

1418
01:01:13,090 --> 01:01:15,173
Can I just boil this once and come back?

1419
01:01:15,173 --> 01:01:17,600
- Oh, this one? You want it to boil properly?
- Yeah, yeah.

1420
01:01:17,600 --> 01:01:18,674
I think that's fine.

1421
01:01:18,674 --> 01:01:20,554
[Chef Gong anxious about kimchi stew heat]
The wind is blowing so much that it won't boil.

1422
01:01:20,554 --> 01:01:23,225
- Oh, Dong Wook, but it might be hot...
- It's not hot.

1423
01:01:23,225 --> 01:01:26,103
Eat the meat first, and I'll boil it up once
and come back. Okay?

1424
01:01:26,103 --> 01:01:27,900
- Have some meat... please.
- It's hot! It's hot!

1425
01:01:27,900 --> 01:01:30,776
[Retrieving it to achieve the perfect flavor]

1426
01:01:30,776 --> 01:01:33,528
- What on earth is that dish?
- Yeah, I'm so curious about the taste.

1427
01:01:33,528 --> 01:01:35,048
He seems to care about it a lot.

1428
01:01:35,048 --> 01:01:36,247
[Chef Gong's affection raises expectations]

1429
01:01:36,247 --> 01:01:38,633
- The wind is too strong, so it won't boil.
- Yeah, that's right.

1430
01:01:38,633 --> 01:01:41,065
- It needs to boil well before we eat it.
- Right.

1431
01:01:41,780 --> 01:01:45,557
[Helping Gong Yoo from the side]

1432
01:01:45,557 --> 01:01:48,199
[Lighting the fire
as soon as the pot is placed]

1433
01:01:48,199 --> 01:01:50,450
There you go.

1434
01:01:50,450 --> 01:01:52,897
I just need to drizzle
some perilla oil at the end.

1435
01:01:52,897 --> 01:01:56,431
[Getting impatient]

1436
01:01:58,084 --> 01:02:00,432
[Next step: Prepare the perilla oil]

1437
01:02:00,432 --> 01:02:01,872
That's it.

1438
01:02:01,872 --> 01:02:03,366
[Checking the broth]

1439
01:02:03,366 --> 01:02:05,361
[Checking the heat]

1440
01:02:06,491 --> 01:02:07,599
That's it.

1441
01:02:07,599 --> 01:02:11,958
[After checking all conditions, he leaves]

1442
01:02:11,958 --> 01:02:13,633
[Kneeling]

1443
01:02:13,633 --> 01:02:16,638
Why are you kneeling there like a criminal?

1444
01:02:17,258 --> 01:02:19,944
We mentioned Byung Chul,

1445
01:02:19,944 --> 01:02:24,176
- but didn't think he'd come at all...
- Oh, good.

1446
01:02:24,176 --> 01:02:25,371
You eat.

1447
01:02:25,371 --> 01:02:28,582
[Go Eun quietly takes care of Gong Yoo]

1448
01:02:28,582 --> 01:02:32,315
[Finally taking a bite]

1449
01:02:34,209 --> 01:02:37,587
[This time, Dong Wook is taking care of him]

1450
