1682
01:13:22,339 --> 01:13:23,342
It feels strange.

1683
01:13:23,342 --> 01:13:25,975
I feel like there's this
unusual bond between us.

1684
01:13:25,975 --> 01:13:28,815
- It makes me feel closer for some reason.
- Right.

1685
01:13:28,815 --> 01:13:32,641
I think it's because the drama
received so much love.

1686
01:13:32,641 --> 01:13:35,821
Right, and I think everyone did a great job.

1687
01:13:37,000 --> 01:13:40,313
I think we all have a lot of
affection for the work.

1688
01:13:40,313 --> 01:13:44,813
It was cold, and there were
heavy costumes, and sets...

1689
01:13:44,813 --> 01:13:47,674
- so it wasn't exactly easy on anyone.
- Right.

1690
01:13:47,674 --> 01:13:49,531
I often think about it.

1691
01:13:49,531 --> 01:13:55,290
It was a really tough project...

1692
01:13:55,290 --> 01:13:58,884
The filming where we

1693
01:13:58,884 --> 01:14:01,497
stayed up all night like that...

1694
01:14:01,497 --> 01:14:04,366
I think Guardian was probably
the last one like that.

1695
01:14:04,366 --> 01:14:08,452
Even so, I think the reason
this relationship has lasted so long

1696
01:14:08,452 --> 01:14:12,092
- is that we met that way.
- Right, exactly.

1697
01:14:12,092 --> 01:14:16,174
- So I feel like we really endured through it.
- Right.

1698
01:14:16,174 --> 01:14:18,547
I think it was truly everyone's teamwork.

1699
01:14:18,547 --> 01:14:20,961
Everyone was like that.

1700
01:14:20,961 --> 01:14:24,168
People would say, "They had a hard shoot
the day before or the day before that,"

1701
01:14:24,168 --> 01:14:26,328
and all these war stories would come up.

1702
01:14:26,328 --> 01:14:31,155
But no one ever said they were
having a hard time on set.

1703
01:14:31,155 --> 01:14:35,549
But Go Eun really went through
an unbelievable amount of hardship.

1704
01:14:35,549 --> 01:14:36,802
Seriously...

1705
01:14:36,802 --> 01:14:38,075
What kind of guardian deity is this?

1706
01:14:38,075 --> 01:14:40,851
- My wish to get a boyfriend never came true!
- Your boyfriend is right here.

1707
01:14:40,851 --> 01:14:43,638
To the point where people would ask,
"Did you stay up all night again?"

1708
01:14:43,638 --> 01:14:45,192
There were also so many locations...

1709
01:14:45,192 --> 01:14:48,152
- for Eun Tak.
- Exactly.

1710
01:14:48,152 --> 01:14:52,866
But it's amazing that she never
showed any sign of being tired.

1711
01:14:52,866 --> 01:14:54,366
Seriously...

1712
01:14:54,366 --> 01:14:58,666
[Go Eun, who never lost her smile]

1713
01:14:59,885 --> 01:15:05,337
It was amazing that she was smiling
like a 19-year-old girl in every scene.

1714
01:15:05,337 --> 01:15:07,945
[There's someone here who worked hard too]
There's someone here too.

1715
01:15:07,945 --> 01:15:10,363
Everyone went through a lot. All of us.

1716
01:15:10,363 --> 01:15:12,416
You collapsed at the end.

1717
01:15:12,416 --> 01:15:14,487
Because you caught a really bad flu.

1718
01:15:14,487 --> 01:15:16,345
So we took...

1719
01:15:16,345 --> 01:15:17,346
Yeah.

1720
01:15:17,346 --> 01:15:19,740
- a week off.
- So back then... I was sad.

1721
01:15:19,740 --> 01:15:21,121
- I thought, "It finally happened."
- Yeah.

1722
01:15:21,121 --> 01:15:24,649
- Everyone held on well.
- We really did.

1723
01:15:24,649 --> 01:15:27,628
Oh, we really worked so hard.

1724
01:15:31,176 --> 01:15:37,176
[The times when we poured in our passion]

1725
01:15:38,817 --> 01:15:44,294
[The people who loved those times]

1726
01:15:51,895 --> 01:15:57,904
[Thanks to them, a time that
remains as a brilliant memory]

1727
01:15:57,904 --> 01:16:00,476
- Let's all have a toast, yeah.
- Okay!

1728
01:16:00,476 --> 01:16:03,164
Thank you so much for coming all this way.

1729
01:16:03,164 --> 01:16:05,178
[A day to be thankful once again]
Thank you for inviting us!

1730
01:16:05,178 --> 01:16:07,075
Thank you! Yeah.

1731
01:16:09,099 --> 01:16:11,472
Thank you.

1732
01:16:31,428 --> 01:16:33,962
From now on, I'll ask you some quiz questions.

1733
01:16:33,962 --> 01:16:36,421
Now, all the questions
are related to Guardian.

1734
01:16:36,421 --> 01:16:38,480
Please accept the orders
as coming from my heart.

1735
01:16:38,480 --> 01:16:41,639
- You were truly born for this.
- It's the MC's discretion.

1736
01:16:41,639 --> 01:16:44,181
[Who will MC Sunny recognize as]
If you get it right, I'll call you a genius.

1737
01:16:44,181 --> 01:16:46,534
[Go Eun, the genius who started strong]
- Go Eun! The necklace. - Kyung Hye!

1738
01:16:46,534 --> 01:16:48,324
949 years old!

1739
01:16:48,324 --> 01:16:49,496
Quebec, Canada!

1740
01:16:49,496 --> 01:16:50,900
[Finally, a chance for Goblin]
- Goblin, Goblin! - Go Eun, Go Eun!

1741
01:16:50,900 --> 01:16:52,941
- No, I said it first this time.
- Oh, sorry then.

1742
01:16:52,941 --> 01:16:54,068
- "Are you poor?"
- Correct!

1743
01:16:54,068 --> 01:16:55,083
- Wow!
- Wow!

1744
01:16:55,083 --> 01:16:56,124
[Somehow annoyed...]
See?

1745
01:16:56,124 --> 01:16:57,403
[Continuing without stopping]
Goblin!

1746
01:16:57,403 --> 01:16:58,875
- Goblin!
- Go Eun!

1747
01:16:58,875 --> 01:17:01,096
[The Goblin's competitive spirit]
- Goblin! - Please sit down!

1748
01:17:01,096 --> 01:17:02,963
- Grim Reaper, 300 years!
- Correct!

1749
01:17:02,963 --> 01:17:05,330
[Strangely, only attacking number questions]
December 2nd... 22.1!

1750
01:17:05,330 --> 01:17:07,177
Whenever numbers come up,
he gets them all right.

1751
01:17:07,177 --> 01:17:09,663
[Three people serious about the game]
This really makes me reflect on myself.

1752
01:17:09,663 --> 01:17:12,637
[The guests becoming desperate too]
- Give me even half a point. - Half a point...

1753
01:17:12,637 --> 01:17:15,887
[Kyung Hye tries a bribe to earn points]
You said you liked even this snack earlier.

1754
01:17:15,887 --> 01:17:17,601
Iceland has the Northern Lights,

1755
01:17:17,601 --> 01:17:18,721
[You know how I feel, right?]
and Korea has Yoo In Na.

1756
01:17:18,721 --> 01:17:20,328
I wish this moment would never end.

1757
01:17:20,328 --> 01:17:21,862
- Oh!
- Oh!

1758
01:17:21,862 --> 01:17:24,308
[More serious than ever]
- I love you. - Go Eun, Go Eun!

1759
01:17:24,308 --> 01:17:25,909
It's so white.

1760
01:17:25,909 --> 01:17:27,655
Oh, it feels like it'll be thrilling.

1761
01:17:27,655 --> 01:17:29,709
[Dopamine MAX: careful not to get too hooked]
- It's three points! - Wow!

1762
01:17:29,709 --> 01:17:32,260
This isn't some quiz adventure show.
We all came here to answer questions.

1763
01:17:32,260 --> 01:17:33,766
[Because we truly love Guardian]

1764
01:17:33,766 --> 01:17:34,917
I definitely said this before.

1765
01:17:34,917 --> 01:17:36,831
[And sincere feelings after ten years]
I really think we had great teamwork.

1766
01:17:36,831 --> 01:17:38,538
I don't know how we managed to do it, right?

1767
01:17:38,538 --> 01:17:40,654
We always worried about
each other's well-being.

1768
01:17:40,654 --> 01:17:43,226
And even in the middle of all that,
we kept joking around.

1769
01:17:43,226 --> 01:17:47,346
I think we helped each other endure it all.

1770
01:17:47,346 --> 01:17:48,676
[The precious connections
that were our strong support]

1771
01:17:48,676 --> 01:17:51,724
- Ah, it's been so long.
- I missed you so much.

1772
01:17:51,724 --> 01:17:53,346
I was truly grateful that we could be together.

1773
01:17:53,346 --> 01:17:56,626
I think even after 20 or 30 years,

1774
01:17:56,626 --> 01:18:00,433
Guardian will always belong to all of us.
